title: armenian tossed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into large salad bowl (except last two).
Sprinkle with lemon juice combined with vegetable seasoning or with your favorite tomato dressing.
Then toss.

title: grandma babe's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain after 1 hour and squirt catsup on the top.

title: green bean corn dish
directions: Grease large baking dish.
Drain corn and green beans.
Mix together and put in baking dish.
Combine sour cream, cheese, soup and onion; all slightly pre-cooked.
Spread mixture over vegetables.
Crush 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and mix with 1 stick melted oleo; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: save-your-marriage supper
directions: Cut two pieces of foil (about 12 x 18-inches).
Split potato in half and put in center of foil.
Place chop on top; stack with other vegetables and salt and pepper.
Fold foil, sealing tightly. Bake at 450° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with green salad, tea and dinner rolls and a little dessert later.
Hugs and kisses go a long way.
Good luck.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Stir apple cider and sugar together in Dutch oven.
Tie cloves and nutmeg in a cheesecloth. Add to the cider mixture.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Remove spice bag and add juices.
Simmer until heated.
May be served with cinnamon stick stirrers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine soup, water chestnuts, pimentos and bread crumbs. Mix well.
Add drained vegetables and mix.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix. Cover top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Soft cream cheese and add powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip, then cubed angel food cake.
Put in 9 x 13 pan.
Top this with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: indian relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, carrot, onion, bouillon and water until vegetables are tender.
Scald the milk (do not let it boil).
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Melt butter.
Add flour and mustard; mix until smooth.
Stir into liquid and heat.
Stir in hot vegetables and the liquid in which they were cooked.
Serve hot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; put in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with cooked, diced chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves in well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies. Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Set aside.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 11 1/2-inch) or 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Mix cooked beef, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and the oregano, basil and tomato paste.
Spoon evenly over top.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater, or until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven 1 to 2 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mints
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into shape.
May use food coloring.

title: party punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 35 servings.

title: veggie pie
directions: Press crescent rolls onto a large round pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing on cooled crescent rolls.
Top with peas, small pieces of broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, fresh mushrooms or any other vegetables you prefer. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over vegetables.
Great finger food.

title: beef rouloden(germany)
directions: Combine dill pickles, bacon, onion, carrots and parsley.
Mix well.
Pound round steak to thin.
Spread mixture on each slice of beef.
Salt and pepper.
Roll each piece and tie at each end and 2 places in middle.
(Toothpicks can be used to secure.)
Place rouloden in casserole dish.
Add consomme and red wine.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove rouloden from dish and add 1 cup of water and 1/2 cup flour to thicken to the dish.
Stir and cook on stove top for gravy.
Serves 6. Serve with German red cabbage and potato balls (potato dumplings).

title: summer peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add gelatin and blend well.
Cool mixture 15 or 20 minutes.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In large stock pot, cover potatoes with water; boil, uncovered, for approximately 5 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and continue to simmer 10 more minutes.
Add tomatoes and Wolf Brand chili and heat through.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: smothered quail
directions: Split quail in halves lengthwise and brown in skillet in 1/4 cup butter.

Season with salt and pepper. Top with onions and add light cream. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Remove quail to a warm platter. Blend 2 tablespoons cold water into cornstarch. Add to pan drippings. Simmer and stir until thick and bubbly.
Pour gravy over quail.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Set oven to 300°.
Butter and flour 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time.
Add the extracts.
When creamy, fold in the flour and salt. Spoon into pans and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and butter.
Beat egg.
Add sugar, salt, soda, dates and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour or until done at 375°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, combine chocolate chips and shortening; stir until all is melted together and smooth.
Remove from heat but keep chocolate over hot water.
(Simply reheat water if chocolate becomes thick while dipping fruit.)
Dip pieces of desired fruit into chocolate mixture, shaking off excess chocolate.
Place fruit on waxed paper on cookie sheets and chill in refrigerator until chocolate is set (no longer shiny).
Gently peel off waxed paper and place in serving bowl.
Fruit will become sticky if left out over 1 hour.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Butter and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in half the flour, then the cream, then other half of flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter in pan.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 350°.
Bake 1 hour to 70 minutes until sharp knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan and cool thoroughly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Partially cook vegetables.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with Velveeta cheese.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour 1 stick oleo melted over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian raspberry frost
directions: Makes enough food for 175 men.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Set aside. Beat sugar, oil and eggs with electric mixer until very well mixed.
Gradually add flour mixture, then fold in carrots, pineapple, coconut, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured 12 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: clainy's frogmore stew
directions: Fill large Dutch oven halfway with water; add 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning.
Bring to a boil; add potatoes and bring to a second boil.
Add sausage and corn and bring to boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp, pepper and juice and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Remove with slotted spoon onto a serving platter.
Serve immediately with cocktail sauce.

title: shrimp hilabus(philippino dish)
directions: Wash shrimp very well.
Put shrimp in a large skillet with one cup of water.
Cover and bring to boil for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In the skillet, cook onion in butter.
Add shrimp and season with Season-All, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Cook for another 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Garnish with cut up green onions.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in oven to melt. Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder; stir in milk. Pour batter evenly over melted butter; do not stir.
Mix blueberries, lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar in saucepan; stir and bring to boil.
Pour over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Squeeze all the water out.
Add cream cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Add hot sauce to taste.
Pour into a casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate marshmallow squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, beat eggs with fork and add.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together and stir into mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans; mix.
Pur into a large pan (11 x 17-inch), greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When done, immediately pour marshmallows over cake and pat until smooth as possible.

title: ripe olive cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine, onions and olives.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll in toasted chopped pecans.
Makes 2 small or 1 large ball.

title: easy microwave pecan brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass bowl, stir together pecans, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook for 8 minutes on High (stir after 4 minutes).
Stir in butter and vanilla extract.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Break into pieces when cool.
Yields 1 pound.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; immediately add the sherbet.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in the Cool Whip and oranges.
Chill until firm.

title: rum slushes
directions: Mix hot tea with remaining ingredients.
Freeze.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large stockpot or Dutch oven, combine potatoes, water, bouillon cubes and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are very tender. Remove from heat.
Do not drain.
Mash potato mixture.
Add ham, butter and milk, blending well.
Return to heat and cook over low heat until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate stuff
directions: Mix flour and margarine into crust.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Use largest tub of Cool Whip.
Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix puddings with milk.
Mix together.
Spread on layers.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion and celery and heat until translucent. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in glass 9 x 13-inch pan on top shelf at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in medium serving bowl.
Combine Crisco oil, vinegar, chives, sugar, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Stir until blended.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Add celery, onion, eggs and parsley.
Mix well.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard in small bowl.
Stir into potato mixture. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: seasoned nuts italiano
directions: In 1-cup microwave-safe measuring cup, melt margarine on High for 30 seconds.
Stir in soy sauce and salad dressing mix.
Place nuts in 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
Drizzle margarine mixture over nuts, stir to coat.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in Parmesan cheese; mix well; cool.

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Beat together egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Add to butter and mix.
Mix together dates, applesauce, nuts, spices, flour and soda.
Add to butter mixture and beat several minutes. Turn into buttered loaf pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey jerky
directions: Place strips of turkey in marinade of all ingredients for 6 hours.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Place meat on foil in center of oven.
Set oven on 200°.
Place a wedge in door (clothespin will work).
Bake 10 hours or until meat turns a dirty brown.
Check after 2 hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: tea horns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Dissolve sugar in water; add to yeast.
Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Add flour.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: debby's frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine the eggs and sugar in a mixing bowl and beat until the sugar has dissolved.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour the batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine Egg Beaters, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
In a nonstick skillet, spray with butter flavored Pam. Over medium heat, after dipping bread in Egg Beaters mixture, brown about 3 minutes on each side.
Re-spray as needed.
Makes 5 servings (2 slices each).
Fat:
0. Calories:

title: nonnie's hot dish
directions: Preheat skillet to 325°.
Brown hamburger and drain fat. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Add cooked celery, carrots and potatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.

title: carrot and rice dish casserole
directions: Bring the ground raw carrots to a boil and drain.
Combine carrots with the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Boil fryer and remove from bone, then chop.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips and shredded cheese. (I put cheese in mixture instead.)
Bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add milk and all other ingredients.
Toast bread that has been buttered, cinnamon and sugar on it.
Cut bread into cubes.
Pour in bottom of pan.
Pour all ingredients over bread crumbs.
Sit in larger pan to bake, with 1/2 inch water.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes, turn down to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Instant vanilla pudding can be put on top of it.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Then add milk and egg. Cook on low heat until thick, then add butter and vanilla.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into baking dish.

title: turkey or chicken fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Chill.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips; brown in hot fat in a large skillet.
Remove meat; pour off excess fat.
Stir in cornstarch, water, catsup, soy sauce, bouillon cube and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add meat and onion.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add green pepper; simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6.

title: glorious punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in lemonade.
Add cold water and cranberry juice.
In large punch bowl, pour punch over 2 trays ice cubes or ice ring.
Pour in ginger ale slowly.
Sherbet may be added.

title: nancy's chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a greased tube or Bundt cake pan. In a large bowl, mix sugar, margarine, flour, eggs, baking powder, baking soda, salt, vanilla and sour cream.
Blend well and then add cinnamon.
Fold in mini-chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tabbouleh salad(no mayonnaise)
directions: In a saucepan, pour boiling water over the bulghur wheat. Stir.
Place over low heat and cover.
Cook 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Chill wheat.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange in 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Cover chicken, bake 20 minutes longer.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Mix together.
Preheat greased skillet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: beef barley stew(serves 4.)
directions: Brown meat and onions until done in a large pot. Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until barley is done and stew is desired consistency, about 1 hour or so.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Sauce:
Melt margarine.
Add dry ingredients, onion and milk. Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: bread pudding
directions: In small bowl, marinate raisins in brandy for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat milk and butter in saucepan; set aside.

title: fat free carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray with Baker's Joy or Pam a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients.
Beat at low speed until moistened.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Toss peeled and sliced apples with 2 tablespoons sugar and fill pastry shell, rounding up in center. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix in butter with fingertips until granular.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake 15 minutes in a preheated 425° oven. Reduce heat to 350° and bake another 30 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, salt and milk together, then flour.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Fill remainder of freezer with milk.
Use 5-quart freezer (noncook).

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add butter and vanilla and mix well. Pour into individual serving dishes. This can also be poured into a baked pie shell to make a pie.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly but well.
Separately mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Blend first mixture in with flour mixture.
Bake in two (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until done (touch test).

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in milk, vanilla and melted shortening.
Add nut meats, if desired.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa and sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and pineapple
directions: Boil potatoes. Slice into pieces. Place layer of sweet potatoes in a buttered casserole. Cover with layer of pineapple slices. Repeat layers to top. Sprinkle top with remaining ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy oven pork chops
directions: Cube steak and boneless chicken breast are also good.

title: banana and strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and
stir
until
melted.
Add pineapple, bananas and apples. Pour
1/2 of mixture in large shallow pan and congeal very quickly
in
freezer.
Mix
cream
cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Spread
over
Jell-O
mixture after congealed. Pour remaining half of Jell-O mixture over cream layer and let set overnight in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Spray 3-quart saucepan with olive oil cooking spray.
Over medium-high heat, heat 1 minute.
Add chicken, red pepper, chili powder and garlic powder; cook 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Season
as desired.
Put on lasagna noodles to boil. Stir together cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese,
eggs, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Smear a little sauce in bottom of 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Lay down half of noodles.
Cover with 1/2 of cheese mix,
then half of spaghetti sauce.
Repeat, ending with meat on top.
Sprinkle
Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: big batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl cream margarine, sugars and eggs.
In separate bowl measure flour and soda.
Add dry ingredients alternately to mixture to mix well.
Add vanilla and chips.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add scalded milk and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the egg mixture.
Pour in freezer and freeze.

title: tootie's butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt butter in small skillet.
Add pecans and toast lightly. Set aside to cool. Heat cream and milk.
Lightly beat eggs and sugar.
Stir into warm cream and milk.
Add brown sugar.
Stir over low heat until mixture thickens, about 3 minutes.
Cool and stir in vanilla.
Add cooled pecans to mixture and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown bell pepper and onion in margarine.
Add broth, simmer until tender; remove from heat.
Add soup; stir well.
Add chicken and pimento.
Fold into spaghetti with the salt, pepper and cheese.
Can make ahead and freeze before baking.
Bake in large dish at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Drop cabbage into boiling water and boil 15 minutes.
Drain; put half the cabbage in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half the salt, pepper and sugar.
Sprinkle on the flour, then half the cheese and butter.
Add remaining cabbage and top with remaining salt, sugar, pepper, butter and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and pour the hot milk over all.
Bake at 400° until bread crumbs are golden brown or about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: veggie meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until completely done.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan melt 1 cup margarine. Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa and water, bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. In large mixing bowl combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture and beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, eggs and vanilla. Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: crock-pot chicken ol
directions: Mix together the soups, green chili salsa, sour cream and grated onion. Alternate layers, starting with chicken and then soup mixture and tortillas, ending with soup mixture on top. Cover and cook on low about 4 hours in crock-pot. Top with grated cheese the last 15 minutes. Cover and let cheese melt. To remove from pot, cut from center of pot like a pie and use a large spoon to dip through the layers.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put 100% Bran in boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and cream.
Add buttermilk to soaked bran.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Add All-Bran; stir in rest of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased muffin pan. Mixture will keep in refrigerator in Tupperware for several days.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Butter large casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients, except Ritz crackers.
Pour into buttered dish; sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber lime pickles
directions: Mix pickling lime to 2 gallons water.
Soak cucumbers for 24 hours (stir occasionally) in lime water.
Soak in enamelware (do not use aluminumware).
Remove from lime water and rinse in 3 cool waters.
Soak 3 additional hours in ice and water.
Remove carefully to drain.

title: sea leg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on a bed of lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix with mayonnaise, cheese and add garlic powder to taste.
Put in baking dish.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Wheat Thins or crackers.

title: russian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or cook in microwave on high for 20 minutes.

title: ham and dip plate
directions: To butter and horseradish, add lemon juice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine juice, milk and strawberries.
Pour into pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: baked turkey
directions: You also need 1 large brown paper bag and 1 roasting pan with lid.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on pan or into muffin cups.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Melt the margarine and mix with crumbs.
Press half of crumb mixture on bottom of baking dish.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add sugar and cream cheese to Dream Whip.
Place half on top of crumbs.
Next put pie filling.
Next put rest of Dream Whip mixture and add rest of crumbs on top.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip.
Set aside 1 cup for garnish.
Add pumpkin, milk, pudding and spices.
Mix slowly with rotary beater. Pour in pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with topping.

title: red cabbage
directions: Brown onion lightly in 2 tablespoons oil, mixed with 1 tablespoon oleo and grated cabbage.
Stir.
Add about 1 cup water, bay leaf, cloves and vinegar.
Let simmer for 30 minutes, then add apple-syrup, salt-pepper and wine.
Let simmer for 30 more minutes.
Freezes well and tastes best when reheated.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients slowly for 10 minutes, until slightly thickened.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients (except coconut).
Press 3/4 of mixture in cookie sheet. Spread on cooled filling.
Put coconut in remaining mixture and put on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Bring to boiling point the cider. Add peel of 1 lemon and cinnamon. Sweeten to taste with honey. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicago deep dish pizza
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small saucepan, stirring well.
Place over low heat until well heated.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O.
Add pineapple.
Let set until soft jelly consistency.
Mix together and add rest of ingredients.
Add a few drops of green coloring (if desired), then pour into an oiled mold.
This is very festive for a Christmas dinner salad. Serves 9.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel; mash avocados.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Squeeze lime juice over dip to prevent turning brown.
Decorate with fresh coriander to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kraut relish
directions: Drain kraut dry.
Mix kraut and other ingredients and let stand overnight.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheese rice
directions: Cook rice, then add cheese and mix.
Add other ingredients. Mix well and place in baking dish.
Reheat in oven until hot. Serves 12 people.

title: chicken with sun-dried tomatoes and pasta
directions: Saute garlic and chicken in olive oil.
Add broccoli, tomatoes, salt, pepper and basil.
Add wine, broth and butter. Simmer 12 minutes.
Mix in the cooked bow ties; toss well and serve.

title: lucky cheese fondue
directions: Heat beer with garlic and grated cheese after it's mixed with dry ingredients.
Place in fondue pot and serve with crackers or chips.

title: jumbo burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Roll into large patties, using hands.
Place patties on broiler pan.
Turn oven setting to broil.
Broil 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn patties over using spatula.
Return to oven.
Broil 5 minutes longer.
Serve on large buns.
Yield: 8 patties.

title: fuzzy navels
directions: Heat orange juice in microwave and melt jello. Add liquor. Pour into 1-ounce cups and chill to set.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugars and eggs together.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Last, add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla. Roll into balls; dip in white sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rene's fava bean dip
directions: Heat beans and smash in small bowl with fork or spoon.
Mix in garlic, cilantro, tomato, juice of 1/2 lemon and salt.
Blend. Spread out on flat plate.
Pour desired amount of olive oil over spread.
Garnish with cilantro and tomato.
Toast pita bread; cut into quarter pieces and serve.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix biscuit mix and sausage.
Add cheese.
Work together and form into balls.
May be frozen until ready to bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well and stir in chocolate chips.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
For cookies, drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
For pan cookies, spread dough in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Pour dry custard into soft Cool Whip and mix well.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch square or 10-inch round pan.
Layer ham, broccoli, cheese and onion in pan.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over ham layers.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix together eggs, sugars, melted butter, peanut butter, vanilla, corn syrup and soda; mix well.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips, M&M's, nuts and raisins; mix well. Spray pan with cooking spray.
Drop onto cookie sheet with ice cream scoop.
Flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dough may be frozen.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Mix flour, soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Brush on chicken and leave for 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy salad
directions: Take all of the ingredients and just mix them together.
Easy and so delicious!!

title: oven chuck roast and vegetables
directions: Put meat in large Dutch oven and surround with the vegetables. Sprinkle with dry soup mix and pour canned soup over top.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and strawberry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a small bowl and set aside.

title: salmon cups(good for kids - easy dinner)
directions: *Note:
You can substitute 2 cans (6 1/2 ounces each) tuna in water, drained, for the salmon.

title: chris' refrigerator pickles
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in pan and cover with ice cubes. Let stand 2 hours.

title: poppy seed tea loaf
directions: Beat all ingredients (except poppy seed) for 3 minutes.
Add poppy seed and stir to blend.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in two greased loaf pans or one Bundt pan.

title: pie crust
directions: This recipe makes enough dough for 2 double crust pies and keeps well in the refrigerator for a week or 10 days.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions until transparent.
Add ground round, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until ground round is brown on low temperature.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and put in baking dish.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix burger, basil, salt, pepper and onion together; shape into patties.
Brown in 1 teaspoon oleo or oil.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add to brown gravy mix and 1/2 cup water.
Mix well.
Add patties to this mixture and simmer 20 minutes.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Zucchini may be peeled or not; slice in round or lengthwise. Have zucchini dampened in water or milk.
Shake in paper sack with Fry Magic; have oil and butter hot in frying pan.
Add zucchini carefully, frying until brown.
Turn and brown on the other side.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil little beets until done; peel and fill jars while hot. Make a syrup with vinegar, water, sugar and cloves.
Fill jars with hot syrup and seal at once.

title: potting soil pudding
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Cream butter, cheese and sugar. Blend milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Combine these two mixtures.

title: yogurt
directions: Heat the milk to 190°; remove from heat.
Dissolve the gelatin in the cold water; stir into hot milk.
Let cool down to 130°, then add the yogurt, sugar, vanilla and jello (dissolve jello in a little water).
Take eggbeater and beat well.
Pour into jars and set in a warm place for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Chill in fridge or cold place before serving.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: wild mushroom and bean soup
directions: Place mushrooms in a medium bowl and pour the hot water over them so that they are covered.
Let stand 30 minutes to soften. Remove mushrooms from the water, squeezing excess liquid out. Chop them up and reserve the soaking water.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix together and bake at 450° in cupcake shells for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add raw peanuts. Stir while cooking.
Cook about 20 minutes, until peanuts are done. Mixture will be white.
Add the baking soda and mix well.
Mixture will become yellow golden brown, like brittle.

title: chicken chili enchiladas
directions: Grease large baking dish. Mix all Cheddar cheese, half of Monterey Jack cheese, chicken and onion. Set aside. Dip tortillas, one at a time, in warm chicken broth to soften.
Fill each with about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture.
Roll and place seam side down in baking dish.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Season and cook chicken; bone and cut in bite-size pieces. Place in buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).
Mix soup and sour cream; heat and pour over chicken.
Mix poppy seed and crackers.
Place on top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.

title: diabetic apple jelly spread
directions: Soak 2 tsp. gelatin in 1/2 cup water. Combine apple juice, lemon juice, and cloves in saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer gently for 10 minutes. Remove from heat, discard cloves and add gelatin and artificial sweetener equivalent to 3/4 cup sugar. Mix well to dissolve. Add 3 drops food coloring and mix well. Pour carefully into 2 clean, hot 1/3 pint jars. Cover lightly until cooled, then cover tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: macaroni slaw
directions: Cook the macaroni and drain.
Gently toss together all ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over apples and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: helen's hot german potato salad
directions: Saute all ingredients in skillet with 1/4 cup bacon drippings. Pour over 5 to 6 cooked and sliced potatoes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or hot throughout.

title: butter-baked rice
directions: Bring water to	a
boil. Add salt. Pour over rice.
Let stand (covered) 30
minutes.
Rinse rice in cold water. Drain. Melt butter in
skillet.
Add
rice
and cook over medium heat until butter is
mostly absorbed. Turn into 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with Accent
and garlic salt.
Pour bouillon over and bake, covered, for 45 minutes
at
325°. Add parsley and fluff with a fork.
Add	almonds
and
bake,
uncovered,
10 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in molasses. Resift flour with other dry ingredients.
Add to molasses mixture, alternately with water.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead well.
Roll thin and cut into 2-inch circles.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven.
Cool before removing from cookie sheets.
Yields 10 dozen cookies.

title: raisin pie(two crust pie)
directions: Boil raisins and water together for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to cooked raisins; cook until clear.
Remove from heat; stir in vinegar and oleo.
Cool slightly; pour into shell. Bake at 420° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into tiny balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Bake at 425° for 28 to 35 minutes.
Check cake for firmness.

title: hidden kisses
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Shape batter around each kiss.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: quick mix meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and then turn heat up to brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumble ground beef into skillet.
Cook until brown.
Drain grease.
Add Ortega seasoning mix and water.
Stir well.
Cook to the consistency that you like.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: black and white cookies
directions: Combine butter and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients and sour cream alternately. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown around the edges.
Let cool and ice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the 3 cans of soup together with 1 1/2 to 2 cans of chicken
broth.
Cut
chicken
into chunks.
Mix margarine and stuffing.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour batter over margarine.
Place fruit over this batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: doris' bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in covered bowl (or 4 quart jars) in refrigerator.
Bake as desired at 400° for 15 minutes. Batter keeps in refrigerator 6 weeks.

title: no cook cucumber pickles
directions: Mix together; do not heat.
Fill one gallon jar with cucumbers and onions.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers. Refrigerate for 5 days before eating.
Will keep in refrigerator for 9 months.

title: canned pork sausage
directions: Make sausage into patties and fry, as if to eat, except not quite as done.
Heat pint jars in pan of water on low heat.
When sausage is brown, fill jars; do not pack.
Leave 1 inch at top of jar.
Put at least 3 tablespoons fat from sausage in each jar. Process in canner for 10 minutes.
Remove jars from canner and turn upside down after jars seal.
Store in cool place.
If any jars do not seal, store in refrigerator until used.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of the margarine and corn flake mixture in a baking dish.
Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cabbage, onion and 2 cups of shredded cheese.
Place other cup of cheese on top of cabbage mixture and top this with remainder of the crumbs and butter mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool!

title: fudge
directions: Cook on high cocoa, sugar, salt and milk; mix together well. Turn heat down on medium.
Cook until when you drop in cold water you can pick up soft ball and it will flatten, then turn off eye (do not stir).
Drop in butter, vanilla and peanut butter (do not stir).
Let sit 15 minutes, then stir real good. Pour in 1 large pan, let cool.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Spread small amount of Miracle Whip on unrolled dough.
Lay one asparagus spear on dough
and roll up.
Bake as directed on can label for rolls.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and margarine; mix well. Add nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
(This is very rich.)

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Combine vegetables, stirring gently.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables, stirring gently to blend well. Cover and chill overnight.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Put cup of boiling water in jello.
Add 16 cut up orange peanuts.
Stir until dissolved. Add 1 cup cold water. Put in refrigerator until it starts to set. Pour in bowl pineapple, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole(donna gayle carmichael)
directions: Mix the milk and flour together well.
Add all ingredients. Bake in pan at 350° until thick but not stiff.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except baking soda and hot water.
Mix baking soda and hot water and add to rest of mixture; batter will be thin.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Cook slowly until desired thickness.
If possible, cook in double boiler.

title: men only baked beans
directions: Place into a covered 2-quart casserole dish; prefer a baked bean pot.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of casserole dish and then add onion soup.
Lay pieces of chicken next and then add the mushroom or celery soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together peanut butter and margarine.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until combined.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on wax paper.
Let stand until dry (about 20 minutes).
Melt confectioners coating; cool slightly.
Dip balls into melted coating.
Let excess drip off.
Place on wax paper and let stand until coating is dry.
Makes about 30 pieces.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake until light brown, about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat butter until soft.
Add sugar and blend until creamy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add chopped pecans. Sift all-purpose flour.
Stir pecans and flour into butter mixture.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Dissolve jello in cup boiling water and add sugar.
Stir until dissolved; set aside to cool.
Put cranberries and orange (including the rind) through food chopper.
Add to jello mixture and stir.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Will keep a long time!

title: caramel nut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugars and add eggs one at a time. Combine baking powder, salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and fluted pan.
Cool 15 minutes before trying to remove.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add strawberries and pineapple with juice.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a gelatin mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream or yogurt over chilled gelatin.
Pour on remaining gelatin and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings, 0 grams of fat.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Set aside.
Combine egg, onion, crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper. Add 1/2 of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly. Shape into an oval loaf and place in oblong dish.
Make a depression in top of loaf.
Pour remaining sauce over loaf.
Cook, uncovered, on roast for 25 to 30 minutes. Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
If using a probe, set cook control for 155°.

title: lane cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and then line with wax paper the bottoms of 4 (1 1/2-inch deep) 9-inch layer pans.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Turn off oven; put in cookies and don't open oven until completely cool.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla and butter.
Cook in microwave until thickened.
Lastly, add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with egg white and meringue and brown.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries. Save juice.
Mix cake mix as directed using strawberry juice (add water to the juice if necessary).
Mix about 3 tablespoons of strawberries into mix. Bake as directed.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well oleo, sugar and eggs, then add rest of ingredients. Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Stir well and add 1 package Jiffy corn bread mix.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: lucy's hermit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Coat dates and nuts with a little of the flour.
Add baking powder and cinnamon to the remaining flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Add floured nuts and dates. Line tube pan with wax paper (I use typing paper) and grease and flour.
Place pan of water in the bottom of oven while cake is baking.
Bake at 200° for 3 hours or until done.
Store in a tight container.
Apple slices which are changed often or a sprinkling of wine will help cake to mellow.
Allow 2 or 3 weeks.

title: never fail microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a 10 x 8-inch dish.
Drop oleo onto sugar in 4 or 5 pieces.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High or until bubbly; stir lightly.
Thoroughly stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread fudge evenly in buttered dish and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: spiced mulled apple cider
directions: Put cider in saucepan.
Add the spices that have been tied in cheesecloth bag.
Add the sugar; heat very slowly to a boiling point.
Heat should be so low that it takes the cider about a half hour to come to boiling point.
Remove from heat, remove spice bag and serve steaming hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken noodle and broccoli soup
directions: Heat to boiling the water, bouillon cubes and chopped onion, then add the noodles and salt.
Cook 3 minutes, then stir in the broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crunch Doritos over bottom of deep casserole dish.
Sprinkle cooked hamburger meat over Doritos.
Layer with green chilies, then beans, then mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cover with cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
Serve garnished with Doritos.

title: apple skillet cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Add oil, egg, vanilla, buttermilk, apples and pecans.
Pour into lightly greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with butter or whipped cream.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Bake at 250° or lower in shell until firm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break some cake into pieces and layer on the bottom of punch bowl, then layer the other ingredients in the following order: fruit cocktail, pineapple, Cool Whip, cake, pudding, cherry pie filling, nuts, Cool Whip and nuts for garnish. Refrigerate; may be made 24 hours in advance.

title: oatmeal raisin bars
directions: 1. Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, and soda; mix well.
Stir in butter until evenly mixed. 2. Remove one c. crumb mixture; set aside.
Pat remaining mixture into greased 9-inch square pan. 3. Combine jelly, raisins, and nuts; toss with reserved crumb mixture.
Sprinkle over layer in pan. 4. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: sally's mocha sauce
directions: Put ingredients in fondue pot.
Stir until boiling point. Reduce heat and simmer gently for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in 2 tablespoons rum.

title: layered salad
directions: Cut lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Put on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch serving dish.
Add a layer of cooked bacon that has been crumbled; a layer of finely chopped scallions; then a layer of diced celery.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Dice tomatoes, onion, cilantro and jalapenos.
Add garlic and salt; mix well.
May be eaten with tortilla chips.
Great over scrambled eggs (Egg Beaters) and my favorite, fajitas.

title: grandmother recipe
directions: Mix it all together and you have my grandmothers.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook meat; drain.
Stir together ground beef, onion, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook until smooth.
Stir in noodles and garlic salt.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Get large skillet (size may vary).
Spray with nonstick cooking oil (Pam).
Cut the chicken into strips.
Chicken is to be skinless.
Cook until thoroughly done.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in cooking oil.
Add onion soup.
Simmer until meat is very tender.
Add mushroom soup and heat through.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Add mushroom pieces, if desired.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: smurgoo
directions: The secret of this goodness is in the slow, slow simmering, at least eight hours or more.
This is pretty much of a universal sauce, to Oven Barbecue "fri-chick" or other vegetarian meats, bake in oven at 350° and baste frequently with the sauce.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together, then add 1 teaspoon of baking powder and then mix again.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes in a greased square pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted butter and graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan; press.
Beat together eggs, 2 sticks soft butter and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture in pan on top of graham crackers.
Slice bananas and later in pan.
Cover with pineapple, completely to prevent browning of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Top with chopped nuts and cherries. Make the day before and chill in refrigerator.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth.
Remove stems and chop stems finely; set aside.
Heat butter in large skillet; saute mushroom caps, on bottom side only.
Arrange rounded side down in shallow baking pan.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Combine and stir dry ingredients.
Cream margarine with sugar. Add eggs, vanilla, bananas, nuts and sour cream.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix at low speed until blended.
Pour into greased (Pam works great) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: scandinavian waffles
directions: Sift, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large mixing bowl.
In a medium bowl, mix together cream, margarine and egg yolks.
Add to flour mixture and stir only until flour is moist. In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter. Let batter stand for 1 hour.
Spray waffle iron with vegetable cooking spray and preheat.
Use 1/2 cup batter for each waffle.

title: korean beef
directions: Make marinade by combining the first 6 ingredients.
At least 30 minutes before serving, stir beef cubes into the marinade and let stand, stirring occasionally.
To serve, heat salad oil; add meat.
Cook, stirring to brown on all sides.
Drain meat slightly; place on serving plate.
Sprinkle with soy sauce, then with the sesame seed to serve.

title: marcella's mushrooms
directions: Cut onions, garlic and Prosciutto into strips.
Heat oil and place cut ingredients into pan; saute until onions are translucent.
Cook mushrooms in salted water until tender; drain and add to onion mixture.
Add pepper or salt to taste.
Add heavy cream and stop cooking.

title: hot mexican beef salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in beans, dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes. Combine lettuce and green onion.
Add meat mixture and 1 1/2 cups cheese; mix lightly.
Top with remaining cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: swiss chard
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add chard, onion and salt.
Boil or simmer for 1 hour.
Don't let boil dry.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar.
Add egg; beat. Mix soda with persimmon pulp.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add persimmon pulp, then dry ingredients, to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate chicken for several hours.
Cook on grill until done.
Keep breasts nice and moist.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Mix water, milk, salt, honey, oleo and beaten egg and stir this into part of the flour, then add the yeast mixture.
Stir and gradually add the rest of flours, kneading like you would any bread or rolls.
Let rise, punch down and let rise again, then shape and put in 2 pans (4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inches).
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar in mixing bowl.
Add flour.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Put this mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan with high sides.
Brown 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, stirring every 10 minutes. Save 1/3 cup for the top.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, butter and peanut butter over medium heat; stir constantly.
After melted, fold in cereal.
Take a clean paper grocery sack, put sugar in sack and add cereal, a little at a time, until all cereal is coated.
Keep in airtight container.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges.
Bake in 9-inch square greased pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and pudding.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: russian dressing
directions: Process until well blended.
Makes 2 cups.

title: beef-vegetable stew(slow cooker)
directions: In a bowl, combine tomatoes, tapioca, basil, sugar, salt and pepper; let this stand for 15 to 20 minutes. Put potatoes, carrots, onion and celery in large slow cooker.

title: bacon and cheese oven omelet
directions: Cook bacon; drain.
Curl 1 slice, chop 4 slices and leave others as whole slices.
Cut cheese slices into halves.
Arrange in the bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Beat together the eggs and milk with fork.
Add chopped bacon.
Pour over cheese and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Arrange whole bacon slices on top of omelet around bacon curl.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Add to flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, sour cream, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat.

title: lo-cal chicken primavera
directions: Cook the pasta to your desired taste.
Cut chicken into strips. Chop up garlic clove.
Saute chicken, garlic, parsley, pepper, salt and 1/2 stick margarine in a pan.
Steam broccoli halfway; saute with chicken.
When chicken is halfway cooked, put 2% milk in and let cook until done.
When pasta is done, put 1/2 stick margarine in and mix.
Mix chicken with pasta and, presto, dinner is served.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Stir in zucchini. Sift dry ingredients into zucchini mixture. Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: *If you use self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers or 35 to 40 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix well. Pour into 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: hot salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, but vinegar, into a large pot. Bring to boil and simmer 1 hour or until desired consistency.
All vegetables may be run through a food processor for a smoother salsa or leave chunky.
Add vinegar; ladle into jars and process in boiling water bath 20 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
Add onions to saute.
Cook pepper, rice and tomatoes in separate pots, seasoning each as desired. Drain pepper and place in baking pan or dish.
Mix hamburger mixture, cooked rice and tomatoes, simmering momentarily.
Spoon over pepper layer in baking pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese begins to melt and brown slightly, approximately 10 minutes.
(I like to prepare this dish because I can clean up the kitchen while this dish is baking.)

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 50 minutes or until very thick, stirring occasionally. Store in sealed container in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Spread on toast or muffins.
Makes 2 cups.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir in rice, onion flakes, salt, soup and water.
Place chicken breasts over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake uncovered in a 350° electric oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is golden brown.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Red beans should be soaked for approximately 2 hours before cooking; drain and add new water. On medium heat, bring to a boil; add salt, pepper (red and black), onions and Creole seasons. Cook for 1 hour, then add sausage.
Additional cooking time should be approximately another hour and half.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream
butter; gradually add sugar, using medium speed. Add eggs,
one	at a time, beating after each.	Add flavoring. Add flour
alternately	with
milk (start and end with milk). Pour batter
into
greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour
and
40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove to wire rack.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop small balls on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Separate broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, onion, tomatoes and eggs; set aside.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and seasoning; mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and serve.

title: strawberry mousse(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Mash and force the berries through a coarse sieve.
Add sugar and cook until mixture begins to thicken, stirring mixture frequently toward the last of the cooking period.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and freeze.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, flake into a bowl and blend other ingredients. Shape into a loaf and place in a buttered dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is delicate brown.

title: straw-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Combine strawberries, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and egg mixture together.
Stirring gently, add a little red food coloring.
Pour in freezer and finish filling with milk.
Let ripen for about 1 hour.

title: peach crumble
directions: Put peaches in baking dish.
Add lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar and oleo until it crumbles.
Spread this over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spicy peach or apricot nut bread
directions: Generously grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch or an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.

title: venison marinade
directions: Marinate venison pieces cut to choice for 4 to 8 hours.
Pour out excess marinade and panfry or grill to desired doneness.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Place in blender with ice and mix.
Serve in 8 ounce glasses.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add orange sherbet and mandarin oranges.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order; pour in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean from middle.

title: no roll sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop onto a greased cookie sheet by 1/2 teaspoon.
Dip small glass into flour and press down on cookie. Sprinkle flattened cookie with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream sugar and butter and then add eggs.
Drain the pineapple and add to the mixture.
Cut the five slices of bread into cubes and fold them into the sugar, butter, eggs and pineapple.
Placed in a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift
together
flour and soda.
Set
aside.
In
large bowl of an electric mixer, cream butter, shortening and sugar. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add sour cream alternately
with
flour
mixture. Blend
in
vanilla.
Pour into
lightly
greased
and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes; reduce heat
to 300° and bake 10 minutes more or
until
cake
tests done. Remove
from
pan
and let cool on
rack.
Frost
with Strawberry Frosting and garnish with
strawberries.
Both cake and frosting freeze well.

title: angel icing
directions: Beat egg whites until they hold a stiff peak (at least 2 minutes).
Put first 3 ingredients in a pan and stir.
Put on stove and bring to a boil (use medium heat).
Boil syrup until it spins a 6 to 8-inch thread or 242°.
Pour hot syrup slowly into egg whites beating all the time.
Beat until frosting holds its shape (soft peaks).
This frosting forms a crust, like divinity.

title: upside - down pizza
directions: Heat oven to 400. In a skillet, brown meat and onions. Drain fat. Stir in pizza sauce, pepperoni, seasonings, and mushrooms. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon into a greased 9 x 12 baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over hot mixture; set aside.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In bottom of pie crust, cut 1 banana in each.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix Cool Whip according to directions.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese-sugar together.
Put over banana in crust.
Top with strawberry pie filling.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, together.
Pour in a casserole dish and you can top with pecans for a festive look. This is a delicious lighter fruit salad (not really sweet).

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix together and chill.
Roll in parsley flakes before serving.

title: yummers(for kids to make)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: heath bar angel food cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Break 5 candy bars into small pieces and add slowly into blender.
Chop until finely ground.
Mix candy, Cool Whip and butterscotch together in bowl.
Slice cake into 3 equal layers.
Ice each layer of cake with mixture.
Finely chop remaining candy bar in blender and sprinkle on top of decorated cake.
Refrigerate.
When serving, cut with a serrated knife using a sawing motion.

title: southern style corn bread
directions: Heat
oven
Heat
oil
in skillet until hot. Measure corn meal into bowl and add buttermilk.
Next, add hot oil or
shortening,
stirring	the
mixture at the same time. Pour batter into hot skillet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: forever ambers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes in greased pan. Cool.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crumb the graham crackers.
Mix with butter and 1/2 cup sugar. Pat firmly into 7 x 11-inch pan.
Beat well eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Spread pie filling over cooled mixture. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Delicious!

title: cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl; add cranberry sauce and cinnamon, clove and orange rind, stirring constantly until blended.
Chill mixture until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour in 6-cup mold, cover and chill until firm.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: wedding bell punch
directions: Ice cream and sherbet need to be soft.
Blend cold lemonade and orange juice with the soft ice cream and pineapple sherbet. Serves 30.

title: orange lemonade
directions: Wash lemons well; slice crosswise into very thin slices. Discard ends and seeds.
Place lemon slices in sturdy pitcher or bowl.
Add sugar.
With wooden spoon, pound slices until they are broken and sugar is dissolved.
Add orange juice concentrate, 3 cups water and 1 tray of ice cubes.
Stir until very cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oven french toast
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Melt butter in cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn and bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Keeps in freezer; just pop in toaster or microwave and serve.

title: renae's beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat in round roaster (or any oven-safe pan with a cover).
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not remove cover while cooking.
Can be cooked in a slow cooker but takes 8 or 9 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make white sauce.
Add sliced onion and soup; mix thoroughly. Layer broccoli and soup mixture, beginning with broccoli and ending with soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Soak bread pieces in melted margarine; place on top.
Pour on remaining margarine. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Pour over vegetables and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
In mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and milk and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: talamee bi zahtar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix zahtar with oil.
Brush mixture onto round bread dough.
Bake on middle rack until bottom is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Can be rolled and filled with olives, mint and tomatoes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Bake half of the batter at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, milk and oleo.
Pour over cake. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over cake.
Pour rest of batter over mixture. Bake until done, about 25 minutes longer. Serves 12.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and with butter. Spread dry cake mix over top. Stir slightly to partially dampen cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crusts).
Pour in crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: fanciful fudge
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a saucepan; add butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and beat until smooth; add nuts.
Quickly pour into a greased or wax paper-lined 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm, about 30 minutes.
Cut into pieces. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too stiff, add a little milk.
If not stiff enough, add more crackers.
Make into patties and fry like you would pancakes.
Brown very well.
Use drippings to make cream gravy.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread; don't raise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear one loaf into pieces and drop in pan.
Melt butter and add rest of ingredients; beat in pan over medium-low heat until smooth.
Pour over torn up loaf.
Tear 2nd loaf and place on top of empty spots. Raise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 375°. Cool 15 minutes and turn out on wax paper.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until tender; drain and cool.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Stir and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Grease bottom of a muffin pan.
Beat the egg.
Stir in the oil and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once until flour is moistened.
Fill the muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Mix.
Add pineapple juice and well beaten egg.
Cook on medium-low heat until it starts to thicken.
Stir continuously.
Remove from heat and add butter and flavorings.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Can be frozen for later also.

title: garlic roasted chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, garlic powder, seasoned salt and pepper.
Wrap chicken loosely in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: miraglia catering spaghettini with duck sauce
directions: Finely chop onion and cut Prosciutto in cubes less than 1/2-inch thick.
Put butter and oil in heavy pot over medium heat. When butter is melted, add onion, Prosciutto, garlic and whole sage leaves.
Saute for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove garlic and sage.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Marinate vegetables and meat for 2 hours.
Place onto skewers and grill until done.

title: pumpkin chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheets with aluminum foil. In a bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade, combine flour and butterscotch chips.
Process until butterscotch chips are as fine as the flour.
Pour into a large bowl; add baking soda, Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, egg and pumpkin.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats, white chocolate and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto the foil-lined cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove immediately and cool on racks.
Store in airtight container.

title: layer dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar for second layer.
Combine nuts and Dream Whip for third layer.
Use Thank You pie filling for the fourth layer.
Chill.

title: festive homestyle chowder(fish; low calorie)
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven on medium.
Stir in celery and onions; cook and stir until tender.
Stir in flour, thyme and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes. Bring to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add bacon and crab.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 (2 cup) servings.

title: rocky mountain potatoes
directions: In a heavy pot over medium heat, brown bacon.
Pour off fat, if any.
Add white and light green parts of onions (reserve 1/2 cup dark tops.)
Cook and stir 1 minute.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix butter, cocoa and flour.
Add sugar and milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: fat free honey wheat bagels
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Combine water, honey and salt.
Add to flour.
Beat on low for 1 minute and on high 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into 12 equal balls.
Poke a hole in each ball and shape into bagels.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Boil 1 gallon of water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Drop in bagels a few at a time.
Simmer for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn bagels over and simmer another 3 minutes.
Do not overcrowd bagels!
Do several batches or 4 or 5 at a time.
Drain.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: italian appetizer bread
directions: In small saucepan, cook oil and garlic together over medium-low heat, stirring almost constantly, for 2 to 3 minutes, until garlic is golden and fragrant.
Discard garlic; set saucepan of garlic-flavored oil aside.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, crumble and drain.
Set aside.
Cut up vegetables.
In medium saucepan, combine vegetables, soup mix, rice and water.
Boil for 7 minutes.
Mix sausage with soup mixture.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hot cider
directions: Drop bag in hot cider and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can microwave in a 2-quart covered dish for 13 minutes on High.
As a shortcut, can use precooked chicken breasts.

title: hamburg picante dip
directions: Brown hamburg and pour off fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Stir in picante sauce.
Layer in casserole 4 ounces cream cheese (cubed), 1/2 hamburg mix, 4 ounces cream cheese (cubed), 1/2 Monterey Jack, 1/2 hamburg mix and 1/2 Monterey Jack.
Heat in microwave or oven until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken vegetable bake
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow glass baking dish; season with salt and pepper.
Add vegetables; sprinkle with water or wine. Sprinkle dry mix over everything; seal tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 45 to 65 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hazel's carrots
directions: Mash cooked carrots.
Add chopped celery, onions, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: party mix
directions: Mix well.
Allow to set for at least 1 hour.
Delicious and so easy.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup onion and salt; mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Brown in hot oil; add remaining onions until wilted.
Drain off excess oil.
Add beef broth, tomato sauce, seasoning and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add meatballs and cook until meatballs and vegetables are done.

title: jello cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Punch	lots and lots of holes in cake.
Set aside and heat 2
cups
of water to boiling; dissolve jello in it.
Pour very
slowly
over	cake.
Let
cool
completely
in refrigerator. Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.

title: fideo
directions: Crush fideo noodles into small pieces.
In large frying pan, melt shortening and add noodles, stirring until brown.
Pour in beef bouillon dissolved in water, stewed tomatoes, vinegar, peppers and onion.
Simmer until noodles are tender and soaked up excess juice, about 20 minutes.
Better tasting if made ahead. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together with electric mixer. Add the egg, vanilla and sour milk; mix until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; mix in zucchini last.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: five hour stew
directions: Put all ingredients together in a pan or casserole dish with a tight-fitting lid.
Do not brown the beef.
Do not disturb while baking.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white flour tortillas
directions: Do not sift flour.
Place dry ingredients in a bowl and cut in shortening.
Make a well in the ingredients and add enough tepid water to make a dry dough.
Form a ball and knead until satiny and smooth.
Take slightly less than a handful of dough and roll out in a circle until desired thinness.
Cook on hot griddle, browning one side and turning over to brown other side.
Stack in a covered dish to steam or under a terry dish towel to keep soft.
Makes 10 to 15.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° or a little less until brown.

title: mjadara(lentils with rice and onions)
directions: Slice and saute onions in 5-quart pot in olive oil until slightly brown and soft.
Wash lentils and rice in cold water and drain.
Put all lentils and rice, salt, pepper (to taste) cinnamon and water in pot and bring to boil with high heat.
Lower to medium/low heat.
Cook on slow heat until well done.
Serve with a dash of vinegar if you like a zesty touch.

title: pork chops southern-style
directions: Brown pork chops and onion in skillet.
Place pork chops in shallow baking dish. Drain hominy and layer over top of pork chops.
Pour soup over hominy and top with onion.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave double fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 can milk.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Melt peanut butter chips until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 can milk.
Put a layer of walnuts on top of chocolate, then pour melted peanut butter over top and spread out.
Chill for 2 hours, then cut into squares and eat.

title: turkey tetrazzini(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook spaghetti in 1 1/2 quarts of water until tender; drain and rinse.
Melt butter; saute onion.
Add liquid from can of mushrooms; blend in can of chicken soup and evaporated milk, mushrooms, marjoram, pimento, meat and Cheddar cheese, cut in chunks.
Pour into buttered oblong casserole.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Can be prepared ahead and kept in refrigerator until baking.

title: lyn's cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma verlie's egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together except egg whites.
Beat the two egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 335°.
If using frozen crust, place on cookie sheet to brown bottom of pie better.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place wings in large baking pan.
Pour marinade over wings. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Turn wings and baste with marinade. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Baste 3 times in last 30 minutes of baking.
More flavorful if wings can marinate several hours or overnight prior to baking.

title: make ahead beans 'n rice
directions: Mix beans, Mexican tomato sauce and salsa together in a large bowl.
Cook rice.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch glass casserole dish, 2 spoons sauce mix, 1/2 of the rice, 1/2 of the sauce mix, 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with the cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Heat in microwave or oven uncovered 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: green jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the water.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill 8 hours and serve.

title: chocolate chip mandelbreit
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla and mix.
Add walnuts and chocolate chips.
Mold two loaves on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Slice when ready to serve.
(May be frozen.)

title: seth's favorite easy stroganoff
