directions: Brown ground beef, draining excess fat.
Add chopped onion, mushrooms and soup with 1 can of water.
Simmer until thickened. Add sour cream. Cook noodles according to package directions. Serve stroganoff over noodles.

title: my favorite cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients except sour cream, then fold it in and put in tube pan to cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter together.
Pour into a small casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente and drain.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Chop well with a knife and fork.
Form in 2 buttered 10-inch pie plates.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the margarine and add to the eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Melt bacon grease, margarine and peanut butter together.
Mix all dry ingredients in a large pan.
Mix everything together. Preheat oven to 200°.
Bake 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry angel trifle
directions: Prepare strawberry Jell-O according to package directions. Refrigerate until the consistency of syrup.
Slice cake in thin serving pieces and line bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Layer partially thawed strawberries on cake; pour syrupy Jell-O over top.
Refrigerate until firm.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions, using 2 3/4 cups milk instead of 3 cups. Cool pudding and spread on Jell-O - strawberry layer.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Cover with whipped cream and nuts.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and water with beaten egg yolks and sugar. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles.
Add coconut. Put in baked crust.
Use 4 egg whites for meringue with 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit.
Reserve pineapple juice. Combine juice with pudding mix and Tang.
Stir well.
Combine fruit and pudding mixture.
Toss gently.
Chill before serving.
Fresh fruit may be substituted for chunky fruit.

title: family favorite cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups boiling water. Add orange juice and mix well. Refrigerate.
Grind the cranberries, apples and celery. Works best if using cranberries right out of the freezer.
Add sugar to cranberry-apple mixture.
Let set awhile for sugar to dissolve. Add mixture to jello before jello gets too set.
Stir in nuts.
Refrigerate to finish setting.
Great with turkey dinner!

title: super sunday lasagna
directions: Prepare Creamettes lasagna according to package directions; drain.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, spinach, 1/2 Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs; mix well.
In a 15 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna, half the remaining sauce, all of the spinach mixture, half of the remaining Mozzarella, remaining lasagna and sauce.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Uncover; top with remaining Mozzarella and parsley. Bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: paella valencia
directions: With a paring knife or a pair of pliers trim or pull off the fuzzy beards from the mussels.
Rinse the clams and mussels well and soak them in cold water for 1 hour.
Drain, leaving any sand behind.
Heat a 15-inch round paella pan or a large frying pan.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix. Pour into greased baking dish, 9 x 15-inch.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pork stew
directions: Sprinkle meat with seasoned flour.
Brown with onion.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until meat is almost tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add peas during last 8 to 10 minutes of cooking. Makes 4 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes thinly.
Mix cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper. Dip tomato slices into mixture and place in iron skillet, preheated with grease.
Fry slowly until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cover with brine; let stand overnight.
Drain and add dressing.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add milk; continue beating to right consistency.
Add vanilla.
Spread over cake.

title: apple roast chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Dry and rub chicken with salad oil.
Pour apple juice over chicken. Sprinkle pepper, garlic salt and poultry seasoning on.
Bake in a 325° oven
for 2 to 3 hours, depending on size of chicken.
Baste every 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cover zucchini with water; bring to boil and simmer until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add to cool zucchini the remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients to zucchini and put in 2 crust pie. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
It tastes like apple pie.

title: shirley's dessert
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Crumble cookies.
Put in butter.
Make layer on bottom of pan.
Mix pudding with milk.
Mix ice cream with pudding slowly.
Pour on crumble mix layer.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Crush Heath bars; put them on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool in refrigerator, while chopping up nuts and celery.
Add all ingredients to cooled Jell-O, blending well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or mold.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: clam sauce
directions: Melt butter and garlic in saucepan over moderate heat.
Stir in flour.
Slowly blend in half and half, stirring constantly. Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add undrained clams, brandy and all remaining ingredients.
Heat just to boiling.
Serve over hot buttered spaghetti.

title: marinated swordfish with black bean salsa
directions: Combine; mix well.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: loxley oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie or 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on sheet before removing.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: one pot pork chop supper
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
(More water may be added if liquid does not cover vegetables.)
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into crusts and chill.

title: chocolate fluff
directions: Whip together cream cheese, milk, sugar and cocoa for 3 minutes, then add Cool Whip.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan: graham crackers (whole); add cream mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; drain off water and let cool.
Peel and grate.
Mix melted butter, sour cream and onions.
Mix well. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese on top and cover.
Let stand in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: baked chicken salad supreme
directions: Lightly
toss
the chicken, celery and pecans together. Puree a sauce of the mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and cheese in
a blender.
Toss
the
chicken mixture with the sauce and pour
into casserole.
Top
with 2 cups crushed potato chips. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger spins
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add onions and peppers. Stir in flour and water. Let cool while making dough.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; set to cool.
Add sugar to cranberry sauce; mix well.
When Jell-O is cool, add cranberries.
Mix and let set lightly.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Stir.
Refrigerate until set.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the first 3 ingredients together. Add the vanilla and 2 cups flour.
Mix well.

title: oh-so-good raisin pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light; add beaten yolks and vinegar, then spices and raisins.
Beat well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook slowly until thoroughly set.

title: great sweet potato pie
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender and mash (should be about 2 cups). Add margarine, eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 45 or 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 hour before cutting. Can use Cool Whip or whipped cream as topping. Delicious!

title: andrea's chicken
directions: Remove skin.
Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper on sheet of waxed paper.
Place bread crumbs on another sheet of waxed paper. Beat egg white and milk in pie tin.
Coat chicken in flour mixture, dip into egg mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
In large pan, arrange chicken pieces.
Bake 25 minutes in 475° oven.
Turn and bake 20 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Add 4 quarts water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours, stirring beans occasionally.

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice
loaf horizontally 3/4 way through.
Blend butter and powder
together
and
spread
generously
between	bread slices; butter sides with mixture.	Wrap bread in tinfoil and place in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit leather
directions: *Works well with apricots, peaches, apples, raspberries or applesauce.

title: june's apple or peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches or apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (if making peach leave off cinnamon).
Combine the next 5 ingredients and beat well.
Cut edges from bread.
Cut into triangles.
Place on top of apples
or peaches covering all of the top.
Pour egg mixture evenly on top.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato scallop
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a microwave casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High until tomatoes are tender. Sprinkle with a little of the grated Romano cheese just before serving.

title: cocoa velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and cocoa.
Blend into shortening mixture with buttermilk and food coloring.
Mix until smooth.
Bake at 350°. Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Frost with any favorite icing.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake in two layers.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes starting in cold oven at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; use juice to mix jello.
While jello is hot, add cranberries, pineapple and nuts.
Stir well.

title: keebler club crackers
directions: Break apart crackers and put on well-greased jelly roll pan. Boil butter, oleo and sugar for 1 minute.
Pour boiled mixture over crackers.
Top with chopped almonds.

title: ritzy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart baking dish and crumble 1/2 box of crackers into bottom of dish.
Combine sour cream, soups and chicken.
Spread over layer and cover with remaining 1/2 box of crackers, crumbled.
Drizzle margarine over top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of mixture; coat each piece.
Top with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: doctor bird cake(a.k.a. fiesta cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease tube cake or Bundt pan.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add pineapple with juice, oil, vanilla, eggs and bananas.
Mix until blended, but do not beat.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan on rack.
This cake will remain moist and fresh for some time.
You can also use a 9 x 12-inch pan, but adjust baking time (start checking at 45 minutes).

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ribs in roasting pan.
Slice onions into rings and place on top of ribs.
Arrange carrots around ribs.
Add bell peppers, cut into strips, over onions and pour barbecue sauce over all.
Cover and bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread evenly in large dish. Layer remaining ingredients, except tomatoes, lettuce and salsa. Top dip with shredded lettuce, tomato and drizzle salsa over top. Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: cheese cake dip(fruit dip)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh cut up fruit.

title: haman taschen cookies
directions: Filling:
Can use poppy seed, prunes or preserves.

title: nana's pane cotta
directions: Cut bread into bite size cubes.
Melt butter in saucepot with water; add parsley and grated cheese.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add bread and stir until liquid is partially absorbed.
Continue to heat slowly.
Crack eggs into pot over bread mixture.
Stir well over low flame.
Serve hot with more butter and cheese, if desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.

title: chef tell's german potato salad
directions: You will need 1 large bowl.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco until creamy.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs one at a time and mix after each.
Add flour (that cocoa has been sifted into) and milk alternately.
Fold in nuts and vanilla. Pour in tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mozzarella puffs
directions: Lay out biscuit.
Tuck in 1 cheese chunk and pinch shut. Sprinkle on oregano.
Dab on pizza sauce (2 tablespoons total.) Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Lay out crescent rolls in a large cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.
Mix cheese, mayo and spices until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Top with veggies.
Best if prepared several hours ahead.

title: orange banana bake
directions: Lay bananas in a single layer in a baking dish, sliced side down.
Put remaining ingredients on bananas in order given.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Partially
thaw frozen items.
Combine with rest of ingredients, including juices from strawberries, pineapple and cherries.
Freeze.
Remove 45 to 60 minutes before serving.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Caramelize sugar in small skillet until dark brown.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cook until smooth.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and flour.
Add milk, caramelized sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Cook over medium heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oil and sugars.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to batter and stir well.
Fold in apples, walnuts and vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine the milk, apple juice, honey, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg in a saucepan.
Heat just to boiling.
Add rice, apples and raisins.
Heat just to a simmer. Remove the cinnamon.

title: garden chicken and stuffing
directions: In 3-quart square pan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook celery, onion and carrots until tender.
Add flour; cook one minute more, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in broth and milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add stuffing and chicken; toss to coat.
Spoon into 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Garnish with celery leaves and carrot curl, if desired.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: single pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco with pastry blender; add ice water and mix with a fork.
Handle as little as possible for a tender crust.
Roll out on floured board and put in pie pan.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: Brown chops on one side in hot oil.
Turn.
Add mushrooms and onion; brown on other side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce, tarragon and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover; simmer for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chops to serving platter; keep warm.
Spoon fat from juices.
Measure remaining juices, reserving 1 1/4 cups.
Combine cold water and flour; stir into juices in skillet.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Spoon over chops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stove-top apple butter
directions: Cook on low heat until thickens.
Add red food coloring or cinnamon candy.
Add a few drops of cinnamon oil to desired taste. Put in jars and seal or put in freezer.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add garlic salt, chili powder, onion and bell pepper.
Wilt tortillas in boiling chicken broth. Place tortillas in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add chicken, then soup mixture.
Continue to layer.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except ham.
Dry ham slices with a paper towel.
Spread mixture on slices of ham.
Roll up and freeze for no more than 2 hours.
Slice while partially frozen. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar, flour and butter.
Add eggs, buttermilk, lemon flavoring, vanilla and salt.
Pour into two prepared pie shells and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Will firm as it cools.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg, if desired.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook veggies as directed on packages.
Drain and put in large bowl.
Cut slices of Velveeta and cover top of veggies.
Crumble Ritz crackers and spread over cheese.
Place 5 or 6 tablespoons of butter on crackers.
Put in 350°
oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: To the corn, add Bisquick, salad oil, egg and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Put 1/2 in greased casserole.
Add green chilies and cheese.
Add remaining mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each vegetable
separately and season to taste. Drain.
Mix all three with with mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onions, lemon juice, water chestnuts (sliced) and 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise.
Put all in casserole dish and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are brown and mixture gets real hot through.

title: 15 minute tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Using a garlic press, add all 8 cloves of garlic and cook until golden, about 3 minutes.

title: cheese and pepper toasts
directions: Cream butter with mustard and lemon juice.
Spread on the bread slices.
Lay a slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Slice the peppers into thin strips.
Discard core and seed.
Garnish with a spoon of mayonnaise and sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil cut up chicken with the bouillon cubes.
When chicken is done, pull meat off bone into shreds.
Cook rice in same water you boiled chicken in.
When rice is cooked (5 to 10 minutes), add shredded chicken and last, add your cream of chicken soup.
You can use any kind of soup if you don't like cream of chicken.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Spread on large serving platter.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, olives, onions and shredded cheese.
Serve with tostados.

title: royal orange-walnut salad
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Saute walnuts in butter until lightly browned.
Add to lettuce mixture.
Toss with Sweet and Sour Dressing.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix together the flour, oats, brown sugar, margarine and soda. Divide in half and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Smooth out and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Put 1 can of cranberry sauce on first half of bar and then carefully pat last half of bar on cranberries.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Mash apricots.	Add hot water to jello.
Stir and add 1 1/2 cups fruit	juice.	Stir and add the drained pineapple and apricots.
Stir.
Let
jello
set
until firm.
Cook following mixture until
thick:
cup
juice
from	fruit, egg, sugar, butter and flour.
Cool.
Fold
in	Cool Whip.
After jello is set, top with
this
mixture
and then top with grated cheese. Chill until ready to serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter pan.
Layer sliced apples.
Sprinkle with salt, cinnamon and water.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pat over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green goddess salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least one day to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: honey-nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of about 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat egg. Stir in milk, nuts, oil and honey.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full. Sprinkle with sugar, if desired. Bake
until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Remove immediately from pan.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan (greased and floured) 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Let set 5 to 7 minutes before removing from pan.
Drizzle icing on top.

title: rum cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan; bake for 1 hour.
Leave in pan.
Drizzle glaze on cake; let set 30 minutes.

title: collards perfecto and sweet cornbread
directions: In large pot, boil all ingredients, except greens, in enough water to cover.
Season to taste.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Turn to medium heat.
Add greens; cook until greens are tender, adding water periodically (keep water level at 1 to 2 inches).

title: beef chimichangas
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Lightly spray 1 cookie sheet with Pam butter flavored vegetable spray.
Place 1 ounce Cheddar cheese and 1/8 of hamburger in a tortilla and roll up.
Place on the cookie sheet; repeat until all 8 are placed on the baking sheet, then spray Pam over all exposed areas of tortillas.
Bake in 375° oven until crisp.
Makes 8 servings.

title: leeks wrapped in bacon with herb butter
directions: Wash parsley, dill and chives thoroughly; chop as fine as possible.
Chop garlic or put through garlic press.
Add herbs to softened butter; mix thoroughly.
Add pepper and salt to taste.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix ingredients and add 3/4 cup flat beer.
Let batter rest for 3 hours.
Just before using, add 3 egg whites, beaten stiff. This is a great batter for fondue (gee, does anyone fondue any more?!)
It is very light and crispy, but gets soggy if not consumed as soon as the item is cooked.

title: o'sullivan's soda bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut the butter or margarine into the flour mixture with a pastry blender or 2 knives.
Add the buttermilk and mix thoroughly into soft dough.
Add the currants.
Knead the dough on a lightly floured board, about 3 minutes or until smooth.
Form the dough into a 7-inch flat round and place in a lightly oiled cake pan.
Cut a cross about 1/2-inch deep in the center of the round.
Bake in a 375° oven 40 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: sweet and sour smoked pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in butter in a large skillet.
Pour broth over chops.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, or until tender.
Remove chops from skillet; set aside.
Combine cornstarch, brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar; stir well and add to pan drippings.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return chops to skillet.
Add green pepper, onions and pineapple.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot in hot oil, brown roast (spoon off fat). Stir in mushroom soup, onion mix and 1 cup of water.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook for 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until everything is fork-tender.

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken 40 minutes.
Casserole can be made with breasts left whole or cut up.
If cut up, mix with sour cream and undiluted soups.
Put in a greased 8 x 12-inch casserole.
If whole breasts are used, mix cream and soup and cover breasts.
Mix stuffing with water and butter.
Put on top of chicken mixture. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: seven layers casserole
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Place the ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with a tight fitting lid:

first, rice; second, corn; (sprinkle with salt and pepper) third, tomato sauce; fourth, water and corn liquid; fifth, onion and green pepper; sixth, ground beef on top; (sprinkle with salt and pepper) and seventh, cover meat with bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mark's favorite chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, egg and honey.
Sift flour and spices.
Add raisins.
Add soda to persimmon pulp.
Mix flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Add pulp and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Very good!)

title: fresh fruit cream cheese dip
directions: Mix together until smooth and creamy.
Serve with any fresh fruit.

title: windex
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jug.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix together, beating in eggs one at a time.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Bake at 350°; cool before frosting.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with cracker crumbs (reserve 1/2 cup for top).
Slice bananas crosswise over crumbs.
Place 1/2-inch thick ice cream slices over bananas.
Freeze.
Sprinkle with walnut meats.
Freeze again until firm.
Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool.
When cold, pour over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.
Spread Cool Whip over chocolate layer.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Store in freezer.
Remove about 10 minutes before serving.
Keep frozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp; crumble it and set aside.
Cut broccoli heads as desired.
Mix bacon crumbs, broccoli, cheese and onion (chopped).
Mix mayo, sugar, vinegar with milk to consistency of creamed soup.
Pour dressing over salad and refrigerate overnight.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in chopped onion and slightly beaten egg.
Add milk slowly while stirring, until the mixture is right consistency.

title: texas two-step stew
directions: Cut up the sausage. Combine all ingredients into a crock-pot except the Spanish rice. Add 6 cups water and the spice packet from the rice. Cover; cook on low 4 to 6 hours or on high 2 to 3 hours. Stir in remaining rice from the rice mix. Cover and cook on low 1 hour more or on high 45 minutes more. Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: spaghetti a la carbonara
directions: In a small bowl, blend milk and egg yolks, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper (set aside).

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo and two eggs and place in 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over the mixture in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: confectioners sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla; beat well until creamy.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep baking dish. Mix the flour and milk, make a thick paste. Pour into buttered baking dish. Do not stir. Combine the chicken and broth, pour into the baking dish. Do not Stir. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse.
Drain thoroughly.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool. Combine other ingredients and pour vinegar mixture over them.
Mix well. Store in 2-quart jars in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving. Salad will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole(mom's one dish)
directions: Boil chicken breasts until fork-tender.
Cut in strips.
Line in greased casserole dish.
Mix together soup and sour cream and top chicken.

title: little smokies in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Brown meatballs; drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add Smokies. Dice bell peppers into bite size pieces.
Drain pineapple chunks (reserve liquid); add to crock-pot.
Heat in small saucepan the juice from pineapple, 1/4 cup brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce; stir until thick.
Pour mixture over ingredients in crock-pot.
When thoroughly heated, serve!

title: strawberry delight
directions: Slice cake and line in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Combine pudding, ice cream and milk together.
Pour over cake.
Prepare jello according to package directions; combine with fresh strawberries and pour over cake mixture.
Chill.

title: baked artichoke spread
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart casserole or souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with toast points or crackers.

title: aunt doris' cherry pudding
directions: Blend together 1 cup of sugar and 1/2 stick of oleo.
Add milk, baking powder and flour.
(Makes a stiff batter.) Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put batter in pan.

title: grandmom hanselman's cranberry sauce
directions: Boil cranberries in water until skins are well popped. Put through strainer.
Cook sauce with sugar until it comes to boil (not boiling). Pour over orange slices and walnuts.
Chill.

title: coffee punch
directions: Place in punch bowl and stir until blended.

title: peas
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add orange rind, honey and salt.
Heat, blending well.
Cook peas according to package directions.
Stir water chestnuts into peas just before serving. Heat.
Pour honey mixture over peas.
Stir and heat thoroughly. Yields about 6 servings.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder, then stir in milk.
Pour this on top of melted butter or margarine.
Pour heated fruit pie filling on top of this mixture. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put sugar over crushed cranberries and oranges.
Mix 1 cup hot water to Jell-O.
Let cool.
Drain cranberries.
Keep one cup juice and mix with Jell-O.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in casserole.
Mix ingredients (except bacon) and pour over cabbage.
Top with bacon.
Bake 40 minutes covered at 350°.
Remove cover to crisp bacon 5 to 10 minutes.

title: easy pie
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Put in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix these together well.
Stir in 1 cup flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites, then roll in chopped nuts (1/2 cup).
Place on greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake 5 minutes.
Press thumb in center, then bake about 8 minutes more in 375° oven.
Fill thumbprint with powdered sugar frosting.
I make different color frosting.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 6 large or 12 small muffins.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, pumpkin, water, oil and vanilla together in large bowl, set aside.
In separate bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture a little at a time to pumpkin mixture, blending well after each time.
Pour into a greased and well-floured 8-inch loaf pan (1-quart capacity). Cook for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: raspberry mousse
directions: Beat first three ingredients for 15 minutes.
In separate bowl, beat whipping cream and lemon juice until stiff peaks form. Fold into raspberry mixture.
Freeze.
Defrost approximately 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add cold water, then other ingredients.
Chill.

title: *oven roasted peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each pepper into quarters.
Remove the seeds. Place in large roasting pan. Add olive oil, oregano, salt and pepper. Toss mixture to coat well.
Arrange peppers in one layer. Roast 25 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
(Peppers can be cut into 8 pieces each.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Cube baked potatoes and place in ovenproof bowl.
Pour melted butter over potatoes; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add crumbled bacon, sprinkle green onions and spread Cheez Whiz over potatoes. Place in oven and cook until cheese is melted (350°).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sugar and next 5 ingredients. Place in uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix mayo, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Chop tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower and bell pepper.

title: latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: Coarsely grate potatoes and pat dry with paper towels.
Add onion, flour, eggs, salt, pepper, nutmeg and parsley.
Mix thoroughly.
On griddle or in large frying pan, in hot vegetable oil, place 3 or 4 large spoonfuls of potato mixture a few inches apart.
Fry until brown and crisp on each side.
Keep warm and serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and clean shrimp.
Saute shrimp in butter with onion and garlic about 5 minutes; turn shrimp once.
Transfer shrimp to hot serving dish; set aside.
Add seasonings and lemon juice to skillet and heat.
Pour over shrimp and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
I serve over rice.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 400° for
6 minutes. Cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Cream butter, sour cream and sugar together.
Add flour,
one
cup
at
a time, beating after each addition.
Add eggs
one
at
a
time beating after each addition.
Mix
in	flavor.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours and 10 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in undrained pineapple and swirl it around to fill corners.
Dump in pie filling and swirl it around until layers of fruit are even.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Cover fruit completely.

title: vegetable and dried beef casserole
directions: Partially cook celery, onion, peas or corn and carrots. Drain.
Put part of each vegetable in casserole, then pour some of your homemade dried beef gravy (or frozen creamed chipped beef, thawed) over it and continue with layers.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese along one edge of sliced ham (about 1-inch wide).
Lay one green onion on cream cheese.
Roll into a log. Place toothpicks all along roll about 1 inch apart.
Slice roll diagonally between toothpicks.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush the graham crackers.
Mix with 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Pat into cake pan and chill.
Beat eggs, sugar and butter for 5 to 10 minutes and spread on crust.
Layer on top 1 cup crushed pineapple (well drained) and sliced bananas.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Garnish with kiwi fruit and/or strawberries.

title: pecan hermits
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, and spices. Beat well. Add eggs and milk, beat until well blended.

title: french fried potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle onion, parsley flakes, salt and pepper on potatoes.
Combine soup and milk; stir to mix and pour over all. Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as package directs; drain.
Put noodles in baking dish.
Add chicken.
Pour soup and milk over this.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Crumble crackers over the top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: cold melon soup
directions: Remove seeds from melon; peel and cut into cubes.
Place pulp, cinnamon and 1/2 cup orange juice in a blender and puree.
Combine remaining 2 cups orange juice and lime juice; stir into puree. Pour mixture into a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Coat
cherries,
pineapple and nuts with 3/4 cup flour. Cream butter
and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after
each
addition.
Add baking powder to 1 cup of flour
and blend
into
creamed
mixture; stir in flavorings. Fold in fruit and nuts; spoon batter into prepared pan.
Start in a cold oven. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: queenie's cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine and add to mixture water and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; stir into mixture. Add oatmeal and chocolate chips; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar together.
Add flour; beat.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until firm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Salt and pepper.
Spread in
6 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Mix together 2 cups Ritz crackers and 1 stick melted margarine.
Put over top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Sprinkle more grated cheese on top.
Bake again for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ground lamb curry
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings. Push meat to one side. Add flour and brown slightly, stirring constantly. Add all remaining ingredients and mix in the meat. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until onions are tender. Remove cloves before serving. Serve over hot rice. Serves 4.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator for 3 days.
Mix well each day.
On the 4th day, form into 6 rolls and place on rack of broiler pan.
Bake 8 hours at 150°.
Turn after 4 hours.
Cool.
Wrap in Saran Wrap or foil. Will freeze.

title: cajun grits
directions: Cook grits as per package, then an additional 10 minutes cooking time.
Spray frypan with cooking oil.
Add onion, ham and green pepper.
Saute lightly (approximately 5 minutes).
Add cheese and allow to melt.
Mix. Add cayenne pepper and mix.
Stir in diced tomatoes.
Blend sauteed ingredients with cooked grits and serve. Serves 4 to 6.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan (mixture will be dry).
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In medium pan, add chicken broth, bouillon cube, onions, celery and carrots.
Bring to a boil.
Then add noodles and chicken.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Season with salt to desired taste.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, sour cream, soup, cream cheese and salt until smooth.
Stir in chicken.
Add beaten eggs; set aside.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes; set aside.
Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil, add rice; cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour stuffing mix into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Drain rice, rinse and pour over stuffing.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Add layer of broccoli.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over top.
Sprinkle with crushed cereal.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Great dish for company.
This also can be done up ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.
Bake 15 minutes longer if you do refrigerate.

title: sugared ham slices
directions: Score each slice of ham sides 1/4-inch deep.
In saucepan, combine ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Place ham on grill 3 inches from coals.
Cook 15 minutes on each side with sauce.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Make oatmeal powder:
Grind together oatmeal, salt, baking soda, flour and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients and add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes in an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine; let set a week.
Lasts for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: apple pineapple pie
directions: Make 2 (8 or 9-inch) pie shells.
Mix all ingredients together except for margarine.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pats of margarine.
Lay over top with second pie shell and form.
Brush top with egg whites.
Bake until crust is done (30 to 45 minutes) at 350°.

title: carrot and butternut squash soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan on medium heat.
Add squash, carrots and onion; cover and cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Puree mixture in batches in food processor. Return to saucepan and add spices.
Bring to a simmer.
Add half and half; heat thoroughly.

title: molasses crisp
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; remove from heat and let cool. Stir flour with baking soda, salt and spices.
To the melted, cooled butter, add 2 cups of the sugar, the molasses and eggs. Beat well.
When dough is well mixed, cover and chill 2 hours or longer.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough in small balls, using about 1 1/2 teaspoons of dough for each.
Roll balls in remaining 1/2 cup sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for about 10 minutes, until cookies are a dark, golden brown. Remove from oven and let cool about 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to a wire rack.
For a chewy cookie, bake only 5 to 6 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add sugar, eggs and oil.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in greased pan at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; chop into small pieces.
Mix eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Take sides off bread and cube.
Line bottom of casserole dish with bread.
Then add sausage and cheese; pour egg mixture on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy apple chutney
directions: Chop cored apples, tomatoes, onions, peppers and raisins. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal while hot.
This is an excellent meat relish and it makes about 4 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Bring sausage and cheese to room temperature.
Mix well and add Bisquick one cup at a time, mixing well.
Roll into small balls about the size of a walnut.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream the cheese well, until light and fluffy.
Add sour cream; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat.
Add vanilla, cornstarch and flour; mix well.
Add sugar and melted butter; bake in a greased spring pan in a 350°oven.
After 1 hour, shut off oven and leave in the oven for 1 hour more.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Peel grapefruits.
Separate sections and remove membranes. Place sections in a strainer over a bowl overnight.
Add enough water to strain grapefruit juice to total 1 3/4 cups liquid. Combine juice liquid, sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan. Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Gently brush some of gelatin mixture over pie crust. Chill gelatin mixture and crust.
When gelatin starts to thicken, fold in grapefruit sections.
Pour into crust and chill until set. Top with whipped topping.
Makes 8 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and fat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until dough is smooth.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover, put in refrigerator.
When rolls are wanted, take out and punch down.
Mold into desired shapes.
Place on greased pan. Let rise until double, 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese stand at room temperature.
Mix and add Bisquick.
Add enough water to mix good. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: ranch rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Rice will swell the last few minutes of baking time.

title: easy and quick apples
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray cookie sheet heavily with Pam. Place in oven to heat.
While pan is in oven, clean and cut red skin potatoes in half (do not peel).
Take the pan out of the oven and place potatoes, cut side down, on pan and spray heavily with Pam.
Place back in oven and bake until tender.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, peanut butter, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in rice cereal.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Form balls 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Press into rice cereal.
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to kitchen counter.

title: german style potato soup
directions: In a heavy sauce pot over medium heat, cook bacon until lightly browned; do not drain the fat.
Stir in the onions and saute for 2 minutes.
Add the flour, stirring until well blended and evenly cooked, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add water, ham base, chicken base and sugar, mixing well.
Stir in potatoes and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and gently boil about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add vinegar, mixing well.
Let simmer 2 minutes.
Add half and half cream, mixing well.
Heat to simmering, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.

title: mexican burgers
directions: Mix in a bowl the ground beef, onion, beef flavorng and chopped chilies.
Make in patties.
Grill, broil or fry.
Place on buns.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: labor day dove breasts
directions: Prepare dove breasts by filleting meat from the breast bone. Place the breast fillets into a medium size bowl.
Add the 1/4 cup soy sauce and 1 clove of garlic to the bowl.
Let set for 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, parsley flakes, bread crumbs, Cheddar cheese, egg, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° until light brown. Yield: 6 servings.

title: amy's peanut butter cookie balls
directions: Mix by hand; roll into balls.
Dip in confectioners sugar; let harden in the refrigerator.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil in bowl until light.
Add pumpkin. Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Add mincemeat, water and pecans.
Beat until well mixed.
Spoon into 4 well-oiled 1-pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool bread in cans. Yields 48 slices.

title: honey mustard
directions: Whip all ingredients together and chill.

title: buckeye candy
directions: In a large bowl, mix together butter, powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll into small balls and place on waxed paper.
In a double boiler or microwave, melt chocolate.
Dip each ball into chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: california taco salad
directions: Mix and toss the tomatoes, onions and lettuce in a bowl. Place chips on a large plate.
Put chili on the chips.
Add the cheese and salad mixture next.
This makes a real tasty salad.

title: "mac" punch
directions: Simply combine all ingredients.

title: candy cane cookie
directions: Shape cookie dough into a candy cane on a well greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle the white chocolate morsels evenly on candy cane.
Sprinkle chopped peppermints in stripes over white morsels.
Slice with a pizza cutter to serve.

title: chicken breast with dried beef or ham
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with chopped meat.
Wrap each piece of chicken with 1/2 strip of bacon. Place in pan on beef or ham.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup, then pour over chicken.
Do not salt because bacon and beef supply what is necessary.
Cook, uncovered, for about an hour at 300° to 325°.

title: creamed corn
directions: Gently scrape corn with a knife.
Get all kernels off.
Put into fatback grease in pan.
Add butter.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in milk and flour.
Cook 5 more minutes on low.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs and breadcrumbs.
Press sausage and seasoning mixture around hard-boiled eggs.
Roll egg in beaten eggs, then in breadcrumbs.
Cook one at a time in 350° deep fryer, 4 to 5 minutes.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cut chicken up and cook (boil or stir-fry); set aside.
In saucepan, cook soup and sour cream.
Add milk to thin out if necessary.
Add chopped celery and cooked chicken.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.
Serves 2.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan. Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer. Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Pat butter on top.
Bake 48 to 53 minutes.

title: steak and vegetable kabobs
directions: In large resealable bag, combine ketchup, oil, vinegar, seasonings and Worcestershire sauce; set aside. Cut steak into 1-inch cubes (trim fat off if necessary). Add meat and vegetables to ketchup marinade. Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate overnight.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend until liquified.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press in pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: squid salad(insalata di calamira)
directions: Cut bodies of squid crosswise, making 1/2-inch circles. Cut tentacles in fourths.
Add squid pieces to boiling, salted water. Boil for 1 to 2
minutes
(squid will curl) and drain. Rinse under cold water and
drain
again.
In
large bowl, mix together squid, onion, olives,
parsley and garlic.
In shaker jar
mix
remaining ingredients,
except
for
lettuce.
Pour dressing over salad and toss
over squid.
Let marinate for at least 1 hour or more.
To serve, line bowl with lettuce leaves and mound squid
on
top. Squeeze
juice from lemon on top of squid.
Makes 8
servings. This is also great on an antipasto platter.

title: beer roast(just delicious)
directions: In small cup, combine chili powder, cumin, salt, sugar, cayenne and pepper. Rub evenly over outside and in cavities of chicken. If desired, rub some under skin over breasts and legs. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 1 stick soft butter, hash browns, sour cream, cheese soup and onion.
Pour contents into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: In a microwave bowl, cook the almond bark for 1 minute.
Add chocolate chips and cook 2 minutes.
Mix together and add peanuts. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: gilhorn cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop cookies on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: bombay chicken
directions: Remove white tendon from tender pieces and dredge in flour, salt and paprika mixture.
Brown tender pieces in hot canola oil and remove to a covered baking dish.
Combine sherry, brown sugar, soy sauce, sesame oil and ginger in a blender and blend 1 minute. Mix in sesame seed and pour over chicken pieces.
Mix to coat pieces and bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat flour and eggs until smooth.
Add spinach, cheese and salt.
Place in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Let set a few minutes before cutting.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and broth to thicken.
Add mushrooms, chicken and broccoli.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serve over rice.

title: tropical ice cap
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in blender until thick and smooth. Makes 1 quart.
Garnish glasses with orange slices.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles and divide.
Brown meat and drain off grease. Stir in sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spread each noodle with 1/4 cup meat sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Carefully roll up each noodle and place seam side down in pan.
Spoon on remaining meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all in 1 gallon milk jug.
Finish filling with water. Freeze.
When ready to use, thaw and add 1 bottle ginger ale. Makes a yellow punch.

title: o' henrys
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and peanut butter in heavy saucepan; cook until mixed.
Remove from heat.
Add corn flakes, peanuts and Rice Krispies; mix well.
Cool; shape into balls.
Dip into melted chocolate and wax.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: dieter's salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese, then add drained fruit and mix.
Last, fold in all of Cool Whip.
May be served immediately, or later.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: While macaroni is cooking, brown hamburger meat, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce and ketchup.
Put in casserole dish.
Garnish with cheese (sharp or Mozzarella).
Kids love this.

title: eagle brand pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: party peas
directions: Pour peas into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add milk. Cover with cheese.
Broil in medium heat until very light brown. Garnish with paprika.

title: cheese and sausage biscuits
directions: Fry sausage slow and crumble.
Drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together with your hands.
Roll into balls, about 2 tablespoons per ball.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until brown. Can be shaped into balls and freeze for later baking.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Dump all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Cool before serving.

title: alice's corn meal muffin
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, then add oil (shortening). Combine milk and beaten egg into first mixture, just enough to moisten well.
Fill greased muffin pan.
Fill only 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes.

title: inch salad
directions: Layer ingredients into a large deep casserole dish.
Sprinkle Good Seasons mix after last layer is complete.
Over all of this spread Miracle Whip as icing over top.
Chill at least and no less than 8 hours.
Mix well before serving.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add milk and egg.
Beat until smooth; add shortening.
Pour in skillet with small amount of heated oil.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: florentine stuffed shells
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together cornstarch and 1 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove 1 cup sauce and set aside.
Stir Swiss cheese into remaining sauce until melted.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Spray 2 cookie sheets with oil and keep warm in a low oven. Need candy thermometer.

title: 4 hour beef stew
directions: Drain one pint of oysters thoroughly by laying them on a dry cloth and wiping all liquor off; a cheesecloth is best.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dip in bread crumbs, then into beaten egg into which one tablespoon of water has been added.
Dip again into bread crumbs and fry in smoking hot fat.
Drain on brown paper to absorb fat.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix together vanilla pudding and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip (save some Cool Whip to go on top), sour cream and sugar. Alternate layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Add rest of Cool Whip to top.
Garnish with vanilla wafers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic.
In a large saucepan, combine meat mixture with undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans and all seasonings.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: emmaus cookies
directions: Mix and add M&M's, chocolate chips, raisins, nuts or anything else you choose.
Drop by teaspoon on a sprayed lightly cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbages
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and core cabbage.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Steam for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain and place into a casserole dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a saucepan; add flour and stir 2 minutes.
Add the milk and blend with a whisk.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes until smooth.
Remove from heat.	Mix ham, bacon, remaining butter and green pepper.
Spread evenly over cabbage.	Sprinkle on the cracker crumbs and top with white sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes until light brown and bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate-oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together; then add other ingredients and cook slowly in a large pan, stirring constantly until well mixed. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix peas, lettuce, celery and green pepper.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream and spread over lettuce layer.
Top with cheese. Sprinkle with sugar and bacon bits.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cream cheese, onions and beef together.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill for at least one hour.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour over flank steak.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Discard marinade.
Grill or broil steak.
Serve thinly sliced with your favorite potato dish.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix ingredients and add butter.
Bake 10 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: lettuce and pea salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients the night before and refrigerate. Cook peas until tender; drain and cool completely.	Toss lettuce, onion, peas and dressing together.	Layer bacon bits and cheese on top.

title: pumpkin cheesecake pie(low cholesterol)
directions: In 9-inch pie plate, combine gingersnap crumbs and brown sugar. Drizzle with melted butter.
Pat crumbs onto bottom and up sides of pan for crust.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown hamburger and taco seasoning.
Mix other ingredients in crock-pot until boiling.
Mixture will be thick.
Pour in hamburger and stir.
Serve over chips.

title: fancy fruit pizza
directions: Cream shortening, powdered sugar, egg and flavorings until smooth and creamy.
Stir dry ingredients.
Chill several hours. Roll into circle to fit pizza pan, 12 to 14-inch.
Bake at 175° for 15 minutes or until edges turn brown.
Remove and cool.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions; drain.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar. Boil 5 minutes and can while hot.
Add your desired amount of hot pepper in case you choose hot relish.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop from teaspoon onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Wash shrimp; blend all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: In medium bowl, soften oleo and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
Crush Oreos and set aside.
In large bowl, measure milk, then mix in pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip and add cream cheese mixture.

title: dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion; drain and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour corn and tomatoes on top of ground beef mixture.
Cover with crushed saltines, adding a dab of butter. Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until saltines are brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Marinate all ingredients (except bacon) for 2 hours.
Drain and add bacon to serve.

title: garlic marinade
directions: Mix and store in tightly covered jar.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine reserved pineapple juice, pudding mix and breakfast drink; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine all the fruit.
Fold juice mixture into fruit.
Refrigerate before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Mix all together and serve hot in chafing dish with rippled potato chips for dipping.

title: sunburst vegetable pizza
directions: Unfold pie crust and place on several layers of paper toweling.
Prick with fork several times.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer doughy, rotating crust once. Cool 3 to 5 minutes.
Invert onto 12-inch serving plate.
Peel off paper toweling.
Microwave on High the cream cheese in uncovered microwave-safe bowl 30 to 45 seconds or until softened. Blend in milk, dill weed and garlic powder.
Spread over crust.
Place egg in microwave-safe custard cup; prick yolk. Cover with plastic wrap.

Microwave on Low (30%) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until set. Uncover and cool about 5 minutes. Chop egg and arrange in center of crust. Arrange zucchini in circle around egg. Place carrot in a circle around zucchini and then arrange a circle of overlapped radish slices.
Sprinkle parsley on very edge. Refrigerate until served.
Cut into 16 wedges using pizza cutter or kitchen shears.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: beef short ribs
directions: Rub 8 to 12 beef short ribs with Gravy Master and brown in a large frypan.
After turning, add the garlic, onions and celery. While this is browning, mix together all the other ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over the ribs and mix well.
Cover and simmer for a couple of hours, turning often.
Add water, if it gets too thick. Serve over noodles.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix next three ingredients together.
Mix all together with apples.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peanutty crunch
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; mix in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes. Drop from a spoon on plate.
This candy is better if you use crunchy peanut butter.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn at about 12 minutes.

title: chicago shrimp
directions: Cook, peel and devein shrimp.
Cut each in half lengthwise. Overlap the cut shrimp in an au gratin dish.
Mix butter, onion, garlic, parsley, salt, tarragon and sherry in a saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Pour over the shrimp; top with crumbs and broil until browned.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Clean the mushrooms and slice vertically into 1/4-inch slices. Peel the shallots and mince finely.
Set these items aside.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Pat chicken dry and pound to flatten slightly.
Dust chicken with 1/2 cup flour and dip into eggs.
Combine breadcrumbs with 1/4 cup Parmesan and pat mixture onto chicken.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil; brush with oil.
Arrange chicken in dish in a single layer.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: snack mix
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave. Mix Crispix, M&M's and peanuts in large bowl with lid. Pour white chocolate over Crispix mixture and toss lightly. Put the lid on and shake gently.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Peel off egg shell.
Slice eggs lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mix yolks with remaining ingredients.
Re-fill eggs with this mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in the salt and egg yolks.
Add the flour kneading with your hands to make a soft dough.
Pat in bottom of a 10x15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 350 oven or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and spread with jam and chocolate chips.
In a deep bowl, beat the egg whites with a rotary or electric beater until stiff peaks form.
Use a rubber spatula, fold in the chopped nuts and 1 cup sugar.
Spread over jam.
Bake 25 minutes at 350.
Cool 15 minutes, cut into 30 bars while still warm.

title: saucy potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart saucepan, cook peeled and cubed potatoes in salted water for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter; let melt over potatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, milk, cinnamon, soda, raisins, oatmeal and enough flour to make a dough that will drop from spoon.
Do not roll.
Bake on cookie sheet that has been greased at 350°.

title: lemon chicken piccata
directions: In a small bowl combine flour, salt and black pepper, dredge chicken in flour mixture, shake off excess of flour.
In a large frying pan heat butter and oil over medium heat.
Add chicken, cook about 3 minutes per side or until tender.
Remove from pan, keep in a warm place.
Add wine or Sprite to pan juices, cook 1 minute scraping up brown bits from the bottom of pan.
Add lemon juice, heat to boil, return chicken to pan and cook with lemon slices. Cook until sauce slightly thickened about 2 to 3 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and capers.
Serve over mashed potatoes accompanied with green lettuce.

title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Soften butter, mix in peanut butter.
Add confectioners sugar a
little
at
a
time, mix well. Roll into marble-sized balls. Freeze until ready to dip.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix and beat well.
Put in well-greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Press into lightly greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Cool and add topping.

title: friendship cake
directions: First, drain the fruit in a large bowl.
Pour the juice into 3 pint jars.
These are your new starters, one for you and 2 for your friends.
Starter can be stored in freezer.

title: veal piccata for two*
directions: *You may use boneless chicken breasts instead of the veal!

title: macaroon bars
directions: Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups coconut into a well-greased 13x9 pan. Combine milk and extract; drizzle half over the coconut. Unroll crescent dough; arrange in a single layer over coconut. Drizzle with remaining milk mixture; sprinkle with remaining coconut. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely before cutting. Store in refrigerator.

title: favorite bars
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar to melted shortening, creaming well.
Add eggs, flour mixture, bits and vanilla, creaming well after each addition.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan or baking dish.
(You must use this size!)

title: brown rice salad(serves 6)
directions: Mix lemon juice and basil.
Pour over cooked rice.
Toss well. Chill for 30 minutes, then add rest of ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving on bed of romaine lettuce leaves.
Garnish with tomato wedges or cherry tomatoes cut in half and watercress.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts.
Place in a large 9 x 13-inch dish.
Crush 1/2 package of chips and sprinkle over chicken.
In bowl, mix grated cheese, onion, soup and tomatoes.
Add garlic powder and pepper.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Crush remainder of chips and sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt bobbie's fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallow whip, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Beat! Beat! Beat!
Pour into 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese; add margarine.
Add flour a little at a time to mix; add pepper and water.
(If using pastry bag, super shorter.)

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
Do not add salt.
(Taco seasoning and Ranch dressing has plenty of salt.)
Serve with Fritos and shredded cheese.
For variety, add a dollop of sour cream.

title: oatmeal brittle cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift
together
flour,
salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend
well,
then
stir	in oats.
Drop by spoonful
on greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken in a nonmetal dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Barbecue chicken!

title: rave review cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased, floured 11-cup ring mold or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the mixed vegetables, celery, mayonnaise and grated cheese together.
Pour into dish.
Combine the melted margarine, cheese and crushed crackers.
Sprinkle over the mixed vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: *To coddle eggs:
Cook 1 1/2 minutes in barely simmering water.

title: aunt millie's custard pie
directions: Lay out prepared pie crust as directed on package, using a deep dish pie pan.
Add sugar to eggs and mix well.
Add scalded milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and then 15 minutes in 400° oven or until center is pretty well set.

title: german chocolate cake and filling
directions: Melt German chocolate in boiling water; stir until completely dissolved and smooth.
Cream together margarine and shortening. Add sugar gradually.
Add egg whites and beat until light and fluffy.
Mix in chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans
and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice pickles into bowl.
Mix in sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Layer pickles with sugar mixture.
Cover and let stand overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Add seasoning and beans.
Allow this mixture to cool slightly, then add cheese.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Add skillet ingredients; mix well.
Add dressing and crushed chips, again mixing well. Very good served with garlic bread.

title: chocolate no-bake drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats, vanilla and nuts, if used.
Beat hard.
Drop by teaspoons onto
wax paper. Let set, then serve.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: old fashioned white cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Blend with flour and 3/4 cup milk.
Then add eggs, 1/2 cup milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat two minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: aunt bertie's punch
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon jug.
Finish filling with water to make 1 gallon.
Pour ginger ale in punch before serving.
Better if frozen and then partially thaw before serving.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix together and press in spring-form pan.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: candy buckeye balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and confectioners sugar together.
Shape in balls.
Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and salt in bowl; mix well.
Add green pepper, onion, egg and water; mix well.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator for 12 hours or longer.
Stir in baking powder.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil in skillet.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except confectioners sugar. Form into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: crock-pot green bean and ground beef dinner
directions: Brown ground beef.
Slice potatoes into crock-pot; add drained beans, soup, water and seasoned ground beef.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, jello, oil and milk; mix until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Fold in the berries, coconut and pecans.
Pour into three greased 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done; cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine
flour and baking powder; add alternately with milk to first
mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy seasoned noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Boil sugar and water for a few minutes.
Add peanuts and cook until dry.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 30 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Boil chicken, onion powder, garlic powder, Tony Chacheres and celery tops in water until chicken is done.
Remove from water, let cool and cut into bite sized pieces. Reserve the water but remove the celery tops.
In a 10-12 quart pot, saute onions, green onions and celery in a small amount of oil until tender.

title: brownies(4-h recipe)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugars; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour and cocoa.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut hot dogs and biscuits in half.
Cut cheese slices in 1/2-inch strips.
Wrap a cheese strip around the hot dog and then wrap the biscuit around the hot dog and cheese.
Arrange on a cookie sheet and bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar slowly, creaming it until light. Slowly stir in syrup, eggs, vanilla and 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Pour into shell.
Top with rest of pecans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese cake shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Cream together peanut butter, sugar, salt, egg and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Roll in ball.
Press down with fork on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spicy ginger garlic chicken
directions: Combine everything but chicken.
Rinse breasts and pat dry. Brush both sides with sauce and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes, until no longer pink. Serve with rice pilaf and green salad.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Mix together. Spread Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is brown.

title: veggie bars
directions: Cover jelly roll pan with crescent roll dough.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes (at least) until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch mix.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Spread mixture over dough.
Put on top and press lightly into cream cheese mixture the broccoli, shredded cheese and olives.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut cookies into thin slices.
Place on pizza pan so that edges touch.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
When cool, beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cookie crust. Put strawberries on and top with glaze.
Refrigerate.

title: hidden valley ranch burgers
directions: Mix the two ingredients and form into patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Serves 4.

title: dipped strawberries
directions: Wash and stem strawberries. Pat with paper towel until completely dry. In microwave or double boiler, melt vanilla chips with 1 tablespoon shortening. Dip strawberry until 2/3 of berry is coated, allowing the excess to drip off. Place on wax paper lined tray. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until set. Melt chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon shortening. Dip each berry until 1/3 coated. Return to tray. Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until set. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Combine the cucumbers and onion.
Stir together sour cream, vinegar, sugar and salt; toss.
(You can also add your favorite raw veggies to this mixture.)
Cover and chill, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 to 4 cups.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna salad casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix soup and milk. Dissolve cheese into mixture.
Mix tuna, vegetables and mayonnaise together.
Drain noodles, then mix soup and cheese mixture in.
Add tuna mixture. Pour into Pam sprayed casserole.
Put grated cheese, almonds and potato chips on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: wiener schnitzel(austrian)
directions: Sprinkle veal slices with seasoning salt. Dip both sides in flour. Dip slices in beaten egg and finally into fine dry bread crumbs, pressing crumbs in well with your hand.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, so that coating will stick when meat is fried.
Fry in 1/2-inch oil at 375° until brown and crisp, turning only once. Serve with boiled potatoes and green salad. Serves 4.

title: old timey chicken stew
directions: Brown cut-up hen in oil.
When cooked, remove from pot.
Add flour and brown slowly to make a roux.
Add peppers, celery and onions and cook until soft.
Add hen and water.
Cook three hours. Add onion tops and parsley and cook five minutes.
Remove hen. Dumplings can now be added (see Dumplings recipe).

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat
juice, pour over gelatin.
Add Cokes, chill until slightly
thickened.
Beat
cream cheese and add to fruits and nuts.
Fold in gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: dill bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for several hours.

title: oyster cracker snack
