directions: Place all ingredients, except the oil, in a brown paper bag and mix.
Gradually
add
the
vegetable
oil while mixing contents of bag.
Put
paper bag in plastic bag to avoid mess. Let stand for several hours, shaking occasionally.
Keeps well in airtight container.

title: green bean supreme casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in butter for about 1 minute, if desired to have onion.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Add milk; cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Add beans.
Spread 1/3 of mixture in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Swiss cheese over beans.
Repeat layers, ending with beans.
Combine crumbs and butter; toss.
Top beans with crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: roast beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with cracker wafers.

title: ranchero chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients; top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until warm.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan on medium heat, mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop onto wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into four layer pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until browned and tester comes out clean when inserted halfway between center and edge of pan.

title: cotton blossoms with crabmeat
directions: Cover sheet pan with wax paper.
Dust lightly with cornstarch. Set aside.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise together. Stir into the cabbage and carrots. Chill and serve.

title: russian round rocks cookies
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. and check the rum again for quality.
It must be just right.
Try it again.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and beat again.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and oleo or butter.
Beat; then add flour and sugar.
Beat.
Then beat the egg whites and fold in.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie("low-fat")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large covered saucepan over medium heat, cook potatoes and carrots in about 2 cups water for about 14 minutes; drain and mix chicken (cooked), carrots, potatoes and peas in baking dish.
In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter, flour and chicken broth and stir constantly until thickens. Bring to a good boil and pour over chicken and vegetable mixture. Place biscuits on top.
Bake until biscuits are done.

title: beef pot stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 5 hours at 270°.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Peel squash; cut into thin slices.
Measure 6 cups sliced zucchini into a large kettle.
Add lemon juice, peel and crushed pineapple.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, until squash is tender but holds its shape, about 15 minutes.
Add fruit pectin.
Place over high heat and bring to boil.
Stir in sugar and ginger.
Bring to full rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off any foam.
Stir and skim for 5 minutes to cool and prevent fruit from floating.
Ladle into clean jars.
Seal with paraffin.
Makes 5 pints.
Good on toast or fresh baked bread.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add chopped pecans and cook slowly until lightly toasted. Set aside to cool. Beat eggs for 1 minute at high speed. Gradually add sugar. Mix in remaining ingredients and pecan mixture. Add whole milk to make 4 quarts.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, then beat 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits. Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Reserve 1/3 C. for topping.
Melt butter and mix with Oreos.
Spread in 9x13 pan, place in freezer for 10 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk and ice cream, pour over Oreos. Place in fridge for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining Oreos.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix cheese, butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir a lot so as not to scorch.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Use as dip for apples, pears or bananas.

title: juniper tea(traditional)
directions: Combine shoots and water in kettle.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Turn heat off and let steep for 10 minutes.
Strain and serve.

title: mama watts' no crust coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs and add milk and flavoring; mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9-inch pie pans or 1 large pie pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top of each pie.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until golden brown.
One pie takes about 45 minutes, less for 2!

title: baked chicken with lemon
directions: Bake chicken and baste with sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered garden salad
directions: Cover bottom of bowl with lettuce.
Prepare frozen peas by pouring hot water over the peas.
Place peas on top of lettuce, then chopped celery, then chopped onion.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and curry powder.
Spread on top of salad to edges to seal. Shred cheese and put on top.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add 1 small jar of bacon bits on top.

title: steak marinade
directions: The quantities of the ingredients are variable according to the person.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a good rolling boil.
Pour over warm cake while still in pan.
Remove from pan about 20 minutes later.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let it stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: raisin-rice pudding
directions: Combine and beat well all except rice and raisins, then add both.
Pour into buttered or sprayed casserole.
Set in larger pan; measure about 3/4 inch boiling water into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until set.
Serve hot or cold, plain or with cream or fruit.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans or one bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients together then pour into pan.
Bake 350°F. for 45 minutes.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup. Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes until dissolved. Stir in measured liquid.

Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours until slightly thickened. Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound. Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Makes 10 servings.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except for tomato sauce.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with two strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour the tomato sauce over all.
Bake one hour at 350°. Serves six.

title: potato, cheese and ham casserole
directions: Put sliced potatoes in a saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and drain.
Transfer to 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Return to heat and bring to a boil, stirring.
When sauce is slightly thickened, add cheese.
Continue stirring until cheese is melted. Pour cheese over potatoes.
Add ham and mix.
Be careful not to break potatoes.
Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine,
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linguine carbonara
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and fry.
Drain grease.
Keep bacon warm.
Prepare linguine according to package directions.
In a saucepan, combine eggs, butter and whipping cream over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat after butter is fully melted and when thickened sauce coats spoon.
Combine drained linguine, bacon and sauce and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and white pepper (optional).
Stir until Parmesan cheese is completely melted and everything is thoroughly mixed.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can be halved or doubled.

title: pineapple layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.
Spread drained pineapple on top.
Mix cream cheese and vanilla pudding together; beat until smooth.
Spread over pineapple; then spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: mimi's butterscotch apple dip
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, combine sweetened condensed milk, chips and salt.
Cook and stir until chips melt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve warm with apple wedges for dipping.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: low country boil
directions: Bring large kettle of water to a boil.
Add shrimp boil and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are half done.
Add sausage and corn. Cook until potatoes and corn are tender.
Add shrimp. Cook until shrimp turn pink. (Don't overcook.) Remove from water. Drain.
Place in serving dish. Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning and melted butter.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water. Melt butter. Combine yeast mixture, butter, sugar and egg. Add flour and mix well.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mash cranberries or sauce into jello.
Add pecans, celery and vanilla.
Mix together and set until firm.

title: strawberry ice pops
directions: You also need 12 plastic cups or popsicle molds (3 ounces each) and 12 popsicle sticks.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender and soft.
Drain the water off; peel the beets and cut them any way you choose.
If small, they can be left whole.
Place the beets in a large kettle and for each quart of beets, add a cup each of sugar and vinegar.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Put into cans and seal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes, sugar, vanilla, orange juice and skim
milk in mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed until smooth.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Combine mixed vegetables and onion in medium pan.
Combine flour, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper, stirring well; add to vegetables and stir to coat.
Combine water and milk; add bouillon granules, stirring until granules dissolve.
Add to vegetable mixture and bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat to low; add cheese and mustard, stirring to blend.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: split pea soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Lift out ham shank and when cool, pick lean meat from bone and return to soup.
Discard bone and fat. Add salt if necessary.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
(Freezes well.)

title: lucious apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots.
Cover with water, boil 10 minutes, drain, cool and chop.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 inch square pan. With a pastry blender mix butter with sugar and the 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Pack mixture into greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes. In the meantime, prepare topping.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs; add brown sugar and salt.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add to beaten eggs and sugar.
Mix in vanilla, nuts and chopped apricots. Spread over baked layer.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in bars.
Roll in confectioners sugar

title: better-than-fried chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine crushed potato chips and next 4 ingredients.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise and then coat with chip mixture.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: Combine water, honey and butter in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Place 5 cups flour, oats, salt and yeast in bowl.
Mix. Gradually add warm liquids.
Add eggs.
Add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough cleans sides of bowl.
Knead for 3 to 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, peanut butter and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Drain and crumble. Cook onion that has been chopped in bacon grease.

title: monterey chicken for the grill
directions: Grill chicken breasts with thin layer of barbecue sauce.
Fry bacon.
Chop scallions and tomatoes into very small bits.
When chicken is done, place it in a flat pan (like a cookie sheet with sides).
Pour a little more barbecue sauce on each breast.
Place bacon strips on chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Place in hot oven and allow cheese to melt.
Does not take long!
Bring it out and serve on each plate with scallions and tomatoes on top. Delicious!

title: topping for "do nothing cake"
directions: Mix milk, sugar and margarine or butter.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Spread over warm cake.

title: sugar cookies
directions: At medium speed, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add oil and vanilla and beat until well mixed.
Combine flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Wrap and chill for several hours.
Set oven at 325°.
Grease cookie sheets. Form heaping teaspoonful into ball.
Flatten with glass to 2 inches in diameter; dip glass in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing.

title: tomatoed corn
directions: Cook and stir all ingredients except tomato over medium heat until butter is melted.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes. Stir in tomato and cover; cook 5 minutes longer.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: In a shallow pan, combine milk and egg.
Dip each pork chop in the mixture, then coat with cracker crumbs, patting to make a thick coating.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Cook pork chops, uncovered, for about 8 to 10 minutes per side or until brown and no pink remains inside.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Saute onion and butter together.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add tomato sauce mixture, stir constantly.
Place a layer of meat, then cheese, then sauce and continue layering.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool. Poke holes in cake and add the sauce.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix together cheese, butter, salt and nuts.
Gradually stir in flour.
Blend well but don't overmix.
Turn out onto wax paper and shape into roll approximately 1 1/2 inch in diameter.
Wrap in plastic or wax paper and chill several hours.
Slice in quarter-inch pieces.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned at edges.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: japanese pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onion and salt by hand and let stand 2 to 3 hours. Bring sugar, vinegar and seeds to a boil, then drain squash and onion and add peppers and pimento to them.
Add to boiling vinegar.
Let come to a second boil; put into jars and seal. Process.
Yields 7 to 8 pints.

title: beef noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Prepare soup according to directions on can.
Add hamburger to cooked, drained noodles. Pour cream of mushroom soup over noodles.
Also can use cubed ham or chunks of cooked chicken.
Also can add cooked vegetables.

title: fifteen bean soup
directions: * Do not add seasoning packet that comes with beans.

title: grandmommie's pound cake
directions: Note:
If making plain pound cake, use 1 cup sweet milk and omit crushed pineapple.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler, but don't let the cheese reach boiling point.
Gradually stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve on toast.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix the ingredients in blender for 5 minutes.

title: dream salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add the flour, potato chips and nutmeats.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion lightly in shortening in a large pot. Add the other ingredients and 1 1/2 quarts water.
Simmer slowly for an hour.
Put in jars and cold pack for 1 hour.
Add milk or water when you open jars and heat.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake a white cake, using egg whites only.
Punch holes in cake while cake is hot.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk and coconut milk over cake into holes.
Let cool completely or overnight, then frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: potato salad #2
directions: Boil potatoes in peel.
Cool, peel and cut into large pieces. Combine remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: seafood casserole deluxe
directions: Arrange all fish in a buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup all over.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with buttered Ritz crumbs.
Season with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan and simmer about 30 minutes. Works great to pour over chicken and bake.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, pineapple (with juice), eggs and chopped pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans.
Bake until toothpick comes out dry, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cowboy pocket sandwiches
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Stir in cubed cheese, remove from heat.
Prepare pastry pockets according to package directions.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put approximately 1/3 cup meat mixture on half of each square; fold pastry in half, enclosing filling.
Press edges together with fork to seal.
Cut three 1/2 inch slits in top of each square.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, beat 1 egg; add remaining ingredients. Cook over medium-high, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Coat chicken wings, parts, breasts, etc. on the grill.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat all except shrimp until smooth; add shrimp.
Chill.

title: apple bars
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add brown sugar and oatmeal. Cut in butter.
Spread half in pan and press.
Dot with butter. Spread apples and sprinkle with regular sugar.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
In 8 x 8 pan bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in oven (300° to 325°).
Use candy thermometer.
Cook sugar, water, salt and corn syrup to very hard ball stage (256°). Add vanilla and vinegar.
Cook to light crack stage (270°).
Pour slowly over popcorn.
Mix well to coat every kernel.
Press into balls before syrup hardens.
Use lots of butter on hands as syrup is very hot.
Makes about 1 dozen balls.

title: grandmother's stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut tops off peppers.
Remove seeds and rinse thoroughly.
Brown ground beef.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Stuff lightly peppers. Place peppers in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop 1 quart sherbet into punch bowl.
Carefully add bottles lemon-lime carbonated beverage.
Ladle into punch cups.
Makes 25 to 30 four-ounce servings.

title: good morning muffins
directions: Brown sausage meat, stirring to crumble.
Drain and reserve drippings.
Add enough butter to drippings to equal 1/4 cup.
Set aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in medium bowl.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together the soup, sour cream and chicken.
Combine the cheese and chilies and set aside.
Spoon chicken mixture in flour tortillas.
Add cheese mixture and taco sauce to taste.
Roll the filled tortillas and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, split side down.
Pour remaining mixture(s) over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 tortillas.

title: lollipop sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed. Beat in egg. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Mix into creamed mixture. Cover and refrigerate for several hours. Heat oven to 375°. Shape dough into 1 1/2 inch balls. Push ice cream sticks into center of dough.
Place dough, with stick parallel, 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten to 1/2 inch with large, smooth, greased and floured spatula. Decorate as desired.
Press decorations into dough. Cookies can also be painted.
Mix 1 egg yolk and 1/4 teaspoon water. Divide into 3 cups.
Add 2 to 3 drops different food color to each. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes. Remove to rack.

title: raspberry pecan pastry bars
directions: Combine 2 cups of flour, sugar and salt in a medium bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture turns into into coarse crumbs.
Press dough in an even layer in ungreased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cover for 15 minutes, then spread raspberry preserves over the crust.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to butter, sugar and eggs, then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix
cherry
pie
filling and Eagle Brand milk; fold in pineapple
and
Cool Whip.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: First cook rice and cook broccoli; set aside.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Toss all together with mushroom soup, mushrooms, pimento, etc. and add Cheez Whiz last.
Mix together well and put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add soup.
Boil noodles until done.
Add all ingredients together and serve.

title: macaroni shell salad
directions: Mix together sugar, mayonnaise and mustard.
In large serving bowl, mix macaroni, eggs and peas.
Pour mayonnaise over top and mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Freeze in plastic container or bags.
Thaw when ready to use.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Combine coconut, cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly against bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes; cool.
With mixer, beat pudding mix, milk and sour cream for 1 minute.
Fold in pineapple and marshmallows; spoon into crust.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped topping and maraschino cherry halves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: On medium-high heat, mix margarine with flour to make a paste. Add milk to thin to preferred texture.
Reduce heat and add sliced chipped beef.
Simmer for 2 to 5 minutes on low.
Serve over toast.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Add sugar to sour cherries and bring to boil.
Cool.
Combine mixtures and add pineapple and almond extract.
Pour into mold and congeal.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Mix flour and creamed mixture together and add egg, vanilla and milk. Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a kiss on each cookie until cookie cracks.
Place in oven for 1-2 minutes.

title: the world's best lemon pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Use ice to speed set.
When gelatin is chilled and slightly thickened, whisk in yogurt until smooth.
Turn into prepared crust and refrigerate until set, about
2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.
May also be made with other citrus flavors.

title: peanut butter pie with chocolate crust
directions: Combine the peanuts, graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter in a bowl and pat down into a pie pan.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 10 minutes to toast slightly.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, sprinkle the crust bottom with the shaved chocolate and set aside.
It should melt in, then set up later.

title: layer salad
directions: In a large bowl layer lettuce, cauliflower (sliced or chopped), onion, peas and broccoli (optional).
Spread over top of layers the mayonnaise, shredded cheese, bacon and sugar.
Let set 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Mix together before serving.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown in frying pan, separately, then add 2nd Step.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 8 or 10 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: velvety brie soup
directions: Remove and discard rind from cheese.
Cut cheese into 1/2 inch cubes, and set aside.
Saute carrot, celery and onion in butter in a large sauce pan until tender.
Sprinkle flour over vegetable mixture; stir until well blended.
Stir in chicken broth; cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add thyme and bay leaf.
Gradually add cubed cheese, stirring until cheese melts.	Reduce heat to low, stir in whipping cream, cook until thoroughly heated.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Ladle into individual soup bowls.
Garnish each serving with croutons, pimiento and parsley.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: corn zucchini casserole
directions: Mix eggs, corn and onion with cooked zucchini.
Add half of the cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry topped muffins
directions: Melt the 1/4 cup margarine in a saucepan.
Add the 1/2 cup of sugar and cook until smooth.
Add the cherries and divide evenly into 12 well-greased large muffin tins.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together at medium	speed.	Pour batter into 3 cake pans. Place oranges on top
of
each
layer and lightly cover with cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box. Mix pudding, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. In a large bowl, place layer of vanilla wafers, then bananas and then pudding. Keep layering the items in bowl and have wafers on top.

title: punch
directions: Add 3 to 4 large Sprites just before you serve.
Should serve about 150 to 175.
If it is hot weather, will not serve that many.

title: matterhorn bread
directions: Place a slice of Swiss cheese between every 2 slices of rye bread (sandwich style).
Combine softened margarine, prepared mustard, onions and poppy seed.
Spread over top of loaf.
Wrap in foil; bake for 18 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 16.
Great appetizer.
Serve with Beef Stroganoff.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook 8 hours on high.
About 1 hour before it finishes, take lid off crock-pot.

title: fruit cake(makes one loaf cake and tube cake)
directions: Combine raisins and hot water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, simmering 15 minutes; cool.
Measure and sift together dry ingredients.
Beat shortening until soft.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with coffee or water.
Add cooled raisins and juice plus walnuts and candied mixed fruit.
Grease well and line bottom of tube pan, bottom and sides of loaf pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 325°; loaf pan for 70 minutes; tube pan for 90 minutes.
When cool, garnish with candied cherries and pineapple.

title: raisin filled cake
directions: Cook all ingredients together until slightly thickened. Partially cool (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: hot ginger fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple and reserve 2 1/2 tablespoons of juice.
Put all fruit on paper towels so fruit is dry.
Arrange pineapple, peaches, apricots and pears in 2-quart casserole, then top with cherries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In
a large bowl, cream together the brown sugar, granulated sugar, butter, peanut butter and eggs until well blended. Sift the
dry
ingredients and add to the creamed batter.
Add the vanilla extract.
Mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly.
When ready to	bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into walnut sized pieces.
Press
with
a floured fork onto greased cookie sheet. Bake
for
to
12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool. These freeze very well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, shredded Cheddar cheese, onion and raisins.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Taste and add sugar if needed.
Mix all ingredients together; add bacon and gently stir.
Salt and pepper if desired.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Line greased 9 x 13 inch pan with 1 package of crescent rolls. Mix other ingredients and spread over rolls. Top with other can of rolls. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool. Top with glaze.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and cut into strips.
Use half to crisscross bottom of baking dish.
Cook carrots, onions and celery in small amount of water.
Place half of this mixture on on top of the crescent rolls.
Add a layer of sliced boiled eggs, put small amount of pepper on eggs. Add chicken cut into bite sized pieces.
Cook soup until melted and add chicken broth.
Put enough of this mixture to cover the first layer in the dish.
Repeat the layers of vegetables, egg and chicken.
Crisscross remaining crescent roll strips on top.
Pour remaining broth on top as this makes it brown.
Cook one hour at 350 degrees or until brown.

title: cajun black-eyed peas
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add meat with seasoning. Cook until brown.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and peas.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add onion soup and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Put layer of chips in bottom of casserole.
Mix sherry, tuna and soup.
Spread over chips.
Top with second layer of chips. Bake in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza bake
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and seasoning.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1 roll of crescent rolls, pour in hamburger sauce, top with 1/2 pound sliced Mozzarella cheese and cover with second roll of crescent rolls.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered, or until rolls brown.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat
oven
to
Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: sauteed potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes on paper towels.
In a large heavy skillet, heat oil and butter until butter is melted.
Add potatoes, turning to coat.
Saute over medium-high heat, shaking pan occasionally or tossing potatoes with spoon for about 10 minutes or until potatoes begin to brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium.
Toss again.
Cover skillet.
Cook about 15 minutes more, shaking skillet or tossing occasionally until potatoes are golden and cooked through.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion; drain.
In a large casserole dish, put mixture.
Add corn, tomato paste
and 1 cup water; mix well.
Fix corn bread according to instructions. Spread mixture over ground beef.
Bake at 400° until corn bread is done.

title: chicken over rotini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat milk and egg together.
Dip chicken cutlets in egg mixture and then flour.
Heat margarine in frypan and brown chicken.
Add jar sauce and sherry, covering chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Pour chicken and sauce over macaroni.
Cover with cheese and place in oven until melted.

title: tangy coleslaw
directions: Wash cabbage and carrots and shred to fine texture.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Toss into cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate until time of service.
Makes six 1/2-cup servings.

title: chicken in yogurt
directions: Clean and skin chicken breasts.
Squeeze lemon onto chicken. Add garlic, yogurt, salt and pepper.
Mix well together.
Allow to marinate overnight.
To cook, chop onion and fry in skillet in olive oil on low heat until golden.
Add cinnamon and chicken mixture.
Simmer on gentle heat until chicken is done.
Sprinkle chopped cilantro on top.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Prepare 9-inch pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell. Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Place milk, bowl and beaters in refrigerator overnight to chill.
Set aside jello and hot water to cool and thicken.
Do not let congeal.
Blend together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then add jello and beat.
Whip milk until fluffy.
Add jello and cream cheese mixture and blend.
Add graham cracker crumbs and butter together.
Put cracker crumbs on bottom of dish and pour mixture on top of cracker crumbs.
Reserve some of the crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: pinch-me cake
directions: Mix sugar, chopped nuts and cinnamon in a bowl.
Melt oleo. Cut biscuits into fourths and dip into oleo, then in sugar mixture.
Press pieces into Bundt pan.
Dribble syrup over the pieces. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove cake from pan while warm and eat by pinching pieces rather than cutting slices.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients
Dip chicken into honey sauce. Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 1 hour, basting during cooking.

title: loretta lynn's butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until creamy. Beat in sugar, vanilla and oleo.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Add onion and saute.
Add broccoli and stir.
Add soup and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cheese and stir.
Stir in cooked rice and simmer for 2 minutes.
Put in lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken pecan quiche
directions: Mix
chicken,
Swiss cheese, onion, flour and 1/4 cup of the pecans.
Sprinkle
into
cooled crust.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard and pour over chicken mixture.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour over crust in pan.
Crumble the rest of the crumb mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° until sauce is bubbly and crust is golden brown.

title: green bean wrap
directions: Roll 8 to 10 beans in a bundle with 1/2 slice bacon and place in 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix dry mustard, brown sugar and onion flakes and sprinkle over green beans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: famous crab cakes
directions: Pick through crabmeat to get out any shell.
Mix flour and eggs together until smooth and creamy.
Place butter, crabmeat, onions, parsley and pepper in a deep bowl and mix well together.
Add flour mixture and deep bowl with ingredients to a cooking pot and cook for 5 to 8 minutes.
Shape into oblong rolls; roll in crackers. Freeze.
When ready to serve, deep fry in hot oil 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Saute until brown and tender.
Add already boiled noodles and mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly
cook
broccoli;
drain
and
set aside.
Saute onion and
celery
in
butter until tender.
Add sliced garlic cheese; stir
until melted, and stir in soup, broccoli and red pepper. Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken saute with walnuts
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces on both sides with salt and paprika. Cook walnuts in oil, stirring, until lightly browned.
Remove nuts with slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels, reserve.
Brown chicken pieces well in same pan.
To chicken add ginger, onion, garlic and tomato juice.
Bring to boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving dish and keep warm.
Skim fat; cook, stirring occasionally, until reduced and slightly thickened.
Taste, add salt, if needed.
Pour over chicken, sprinkle with reserved walnuts and parsley.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix butter, egg, sugar and chocolate thoroughly. Stir in buttermilk and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Blend in. Mix in nuts. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: century old pumpkin pie
directions: Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin.
Add oil, slightly beaten eggs and milk.
Bake in one crust at 350° until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in Ranch dressing.
Add chilies, pimentos, Cheddar cheese, olives and green onions.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll "jelly roll" fashion and slice.
Serve with salsa. Looks great for Christmas with the red, white and green!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion and ground beef together.
In large mixing bowl, mix remaining ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake 30 minutes at 400°, uncovered.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Freeze until firm.
Can be used as a salad or a dessert!

title: garden zucchini slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
In large bowl, toss zucchini, onion and apples together.
Pour dressing over zucchini mixture; season with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: southern-fried baked steak
directions: Pound steak to tenderize.
Cut into serving size pieces. Season with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.

title: icebox cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Let cool, take thread and cut layers in half.
Stack the layers with this icing between each layer and cover sides and top and refrigerate.
Mix together the Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar for icing.

title: apple banana bread
directions: Combine eggs, bananas,
sugar,
oil
and
milk.
Combine flour and wheat germ separate.
Add
banana
mixture
to
flour mixture. Fold apples into batter.
Grease 2 loaf pans and pour equal amounts of batter into each.
Bake
at
350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool and remove from pans.
Wrap and store loaves.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with half of margarine and put in bottom of pan.
Saute onions in remainder of margarine and put onion mixture on top of crumb mixture.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over onion mixture, salt and pepper lightly.
Top with grated Cheddar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil, allowing foil to overlap rim of pan.
Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange dough slices in circular pattern in pan, starting at outer edge of pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and garlic powder together.
Marinate wings in sauce for 6 to 12 hours.
Bake at 350° until done and liquid gets sticky.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour and onion.
Add to the spinach, then add spices and sour cream.
Top with almonds and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pecans
directions: Mix ingredients, except pecans.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans until coated.
Pour on wax paper; separate and let dry.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast and dissolve sugar in water; add milk cooled to lukewarm, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Add flour to make soft dough, let stand 10 minutes.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and cover; store in refrigerator.
Shape rolls about 2 hours before serving.
Let rise till double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven 425° for 15-20 minutes.
Punch down remaining dough return to refrigerator.
This will keep for a week or use all same day.

title: cucumbers with dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt. Add cucumbers; stir to coat. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: better than sex
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
Cool.
In saucepan heat pineapple, sugar and instant pudding.
Poke holes in cake and pour mixture over cake.
Add layer of coconut and top with Cool Whip and nuts if desired.

title: cold marinated broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour over broccoli.
Allow to marinate at least 4 hours.	Stir or mix occasionally.
This is even better when marinated longer.	Cauliflower may also be used instead
of all broccoli in this recipe.
Makes a rather large amount.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Stir sugar in sauerkraut.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Stir in other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over bread. Crumble with fork or fingertips.
Add turkey, 1/4 cup onion and black pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape firmly into 32 equal meatballs.
Set aside.

title: savory barbecue sauce
directions: Place butter in a microwave-safe measuring cup or other dish. Microwave at High power for about 40 seconds until melted.
Add onions and stir well.
Cover dish with waxed paper.
Microwave at High power for about 2 minutes, stirring once.
Add all remaining ingredients except thyme leaves to dish, stirring until well blended.
Microwave at High power for another 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once until sauce is boiling hot and thickened.
Add thyme leaves when stirring the last time.
Brush chicken legs, drumsticks or thighs with sauce while barbecuing.

title: luscious lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. In a large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, garlic salt, oregano and black pepper.
In a 2-quart buttered rectangular baking dish, layer 1/3 of noodles, 1/3 of sauce and 1/3 of cottage, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat twice.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: it is beyond delicious
directions: Chop and combine all ingredients except 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Put in buttered dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese with some paprika.
Heat and serve with crackers.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and eggs until creamy.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Mold in 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Cool for at least 3 hours.
Divide into 3 rows.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches, 1 cup sugar and nutmeg in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until peaches begin to exude their juices.
Sprinkle on 1/4 cup flour; cook and stir until well incorporated.
Stir in the butter.
Turn into an ovenproof 9-inch baking dish.
Place remaining flour and salt in a small bowl.
Using a pastry blender (or fingertips), work in the shortening until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in enough water to make a soft dough. Gather the dough into a ball; roll out on a floured board.
Place rolled out dough over the peaches, tucking under the edges or trimming as needed.
Sprinkle the dough with 1 teaspoon sugar; slash in several places to allow the steam to escape.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top is well browned.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces.
Put white sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake to cover.
Place pieces in a greased tube pan by layers.
Sprinkle each layer with pecans, raisins or coconut.

title: butter mints
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand, molding into dough.
Pat small amounts into rubber molds or roll out into "snakes" to cup apart for pillow mints.
Allow to air dry before storing (1 hour or longer).

title: batter fried red snapper or yellow pike
directions: Split the fish open, butterfly-style.
Place cornmeal in a shallow bowl.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Place the beaten eggs in another shallow bowl.
Mix well.
Heat the cooking oil in a large frying pan.
Place the fish in the egg batter, then into the cornmeal mixture.
Place fish in the frying pan and cook until golden brown.
Remove to a platter lined with paper towels.

title: irish-italian spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until golden.
Add meat and seasonings. Simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Add soups.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring often.
Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water until tender.
Arrange on a hot platter.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper. Mix together soup and sour cream. Put 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Fill bottom of 10 flour tortillas with hamburger and part of shredded cheese. Roll these up and put in pan.
Pour last 1/2 of soup mixture over top of tortillas and sprinkle with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jackie's apple dumplings
directions: Heat sugar, water, margarine and cinnamon in saucepan until margarine melts.
Roll biscuits out the size of a saucer; wrap each apple half with biscuit.
Tuck dough under each apple half. Place apples in large pan.
Pour sugar mixture over apples. Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Every 10 minutes, baste apples with juice.

title: pb&j granola bars(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 300°. In bowl, combine peanut butter, milk and honey. Add granola cereal, raisins and cinnamon using hands to mix. Press into 8 x 8-inch baking pan lined with parchment paper. Bake 15 minutes. Cool. Cut into 16 pieces. Coat half the bars with spreadable fruit; top with remaining bars.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Melt butter and mix with ingredients.
Put in cake pan.

title: christmas poinsettia(drink)
directions: Mix half and half champagne and the cranberry/raspberry drink over ice in a large wine glass.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast.
Refrigerate or roll out on a floured cloth and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven on a greased cookie sheet.

title: cheese cake blondies
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next four ingredients together. Pour over the bottom layer.
Then bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: golden cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, 1 chicken bouillon cube and seasonings; mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: yummy chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pudding and whipped topping according to package directions.
Fold together. Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: simple turkey meat loaf(low-fat and lo-cal)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Place in a loaf pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Pour an 8 ounce size can tomato sauce over turkey meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: american lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on box.
Brown hamburger and season to taste with salt, pepper, chili powder and Italian seasoning.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and onion in a bowl.
Mix well.
Layer 1/2 of noodles in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (approximately 5 to 6 pieces).
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture and 1/2 of sauce mixture.
Layer rest of noodles, cheese mixture and top with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach and cheese dish
directions: Make a sauce of mustard, eggs, salt and pepper.
Layer spinach, cracker crumbs, sauce and cheese.
Continue layering until bowl is full or spinach is gone.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat well for 2 minutes.
Add egg, shortening and remaining flour; mix with a spoon or hand mix until dough is easy to handle.
Place in greased bowl in refrigerator. Punch occasionally.

title: english trifle
directions: Mix
preserves,
frozen raspberries (thawed) and frozen whole raspberries (thawed) together.
Layer the ladyfingers in the
bowl with the raspberry mixture.
Continue layering until all ladyfingers and raspberry mixture has been used.
Mix the pudding according to the directions on the box.
Pour pudding over
the layers
and cover with Saran Wrap to prevent a skim from
forming and refrigerate.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with almonds.

title: mr. (charles) oursler's swiss steak
directions: Pound steak and cut in serving size pieces.
Flour and brown steak.
Add olives and tomato sauce; simmer 1 hour.
Add pepper and onion and simmer an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over fresh creamed potatoes with rolls.

title: easter potatoes
directions: Mix all together (except Topping) and put into a greased
9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Combine the corn flakes and melted butter, and spread over the top of the potato mixture.
Top with grated cheddar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar; press into 9-inch pie plate.
Slice bananas over crust. Blend in bowl the Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons sugar; pour over bananas.
Spread drained pineapple over this. Next, add a layer of Cool Whip.
Top with coconut, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: bubble bread #2
directions: Let rolls thaw.
Grease angel food cake pan.
Take rolls and half in three's.
Mix melted butter and cinnamon and sugar.
Roll balls in mixture.
Place in layers in cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts on each layer.
Let rise to double size.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert on plate.
Pulls apart easily.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Cover bulgur with water and soak for 1 hour.
Drain well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: roast turkey
directions: For 4 to 6 pounds of turkey, roast 3 to 4 hours.

title: clay christmas ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Stir in water gradually.
Knead for 7 to 10 minutes.
Add food coloring as desired.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick; cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Make a small hole for hook to hang, place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter pie dish.
Cream butter and 1 cup sugar; add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder; add a little at a time to rest of mixture.
Batter should be thick, but not lumpy.
Spread evenly in pie dish.
Top with fruit.
Press down
on fruit so that it sinks on the batter. Sprinkle with rest of sugar.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Great warm topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: grandma hill's baked beans
directions: Boil beans in enough water to more than cover for two hours. (May have to keep adding water; do not boil rapidly.)
Then, let soak for 1 hour.
Put beans in casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour bean water over beans to cover; add bacon.
Bake at 350° until beans are soft.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef with onion, salt to taste.
Mix together beans, tomato juice, water, and spices.
Add drained beef to rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
After 30 minutes, add corn starch mixed with water.
Cook until desired thickness.
Add spaghetti or macaroni.

title: joshua's favorite chinese chicken
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine the soy sauce, chili powder and garlic.
Add skinned and cut up chicken and scallions (cut into 1-inch sections with green tops), and stir to coat the chicken well.

title: creamy cheesecake pie
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch pie plate with butter or margarine. Flour the greased pan with graham cracker or cookie crumbs.

title: microwave carmel corn
directions: Pop popcorn; put in large brown grocery bag.
In mircowavable bowl mix syrup, sugar and salt; cook 2 minutes.
Stir; cook 2 minutes more.
Add vanilla and soda; stir and pour over popcorn in bag.
Mix good; roll top of bag down and put in microwave for 1 minute.
Open sack and let dry.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry in deep fat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture over melted oleo, do not stir.
Put peaches on batter, sprinkle with remaining cup of sugar over peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon over sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spinach pie parma
directions: Combine croutons and margarine; mix well and press into bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine 1/4 cup Parmesan and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese. Let stand five minutes before serving.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Mix this all together.
Put in casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Use electric mixer.

title: cheesy pasta 'n chicken
directions: Combine noodles, water and salt.
Microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes.
Stir occasionally; drain and set aside.

title: candy corn
directions: Combine sugar, white corn syrup and butter in pan, bring to boil stirring constantly.
Turn heat low and boil 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and several drops food coloring (optional).
Meanwhile, combine powdered sugar, salt and powdered milk.
Add all at once to mixture in pan.
Stir until cool enough to handle.
Knead until stiff enough to hold its shape. Shape into triangles, or any shape desired.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds candy.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place dry ingredients in large bowl, making a "well" in the center.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done. Makes 2 large loaves.

title: one pan potatoes and chicken rosemary
directions: While potatoes cook, in large skillet, toss and brown chicken and garlic in oil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and rosemary.
Saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned. Season with salt and pepper.
Time: 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buckeyes candy
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugar a little at a time, enough to make it stiff.
Mix well.
Roll into balls. Place on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Melt 1/4 stick of Parowax and 1 (12 ounce) package of real chocolate chips.
Keep warm.
Dip peanut butter balls in the chocolate mix and set on waxed paper to chill.
Takes 6 to 7 minutes so coating hardens.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add jello and cook until completely dissolved. Put strawberries into baked pie shell. Pour syrup over strawberries. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomato slices over sauerkraut.
Spread with dressing and dot with butter.
Top with corned beef and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: bulgarian apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Peel and slice apple into thin slices. Place pan in oven with butter, when butter is melted, take the pan out. In a large mixing bowl, beat the eggs with the sugar until it rises. Add the melted butter, flour, dry milk, milk, baking powder, vanilla and cinnamon, beat at low speed until well mixed. Place one layer of apple slices in the pan and pour over cake mixture. Bake until golden brown, or until toothpick comes out clean. Let cool completely before removing from pan. Place on cake dish. Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: country lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour in oleo; blend with electric mixer on medium speed until mixture resembles cornmeal. Stir in pecans.
Press firmly and evenly into pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker frozen cake
directions: Set aside 12 double crackers; crush remaining. Melt oleo. Add to crumbs, which have sugar added to them. Add nuts and pineapple; mix well. Line cracker box with foil. Layer 3 double crackers across bottom of box. Place 3/4-inch layer of filling on them. Alternate in this manner until you have 3 layers of filling and 4 layers of crackers. Freeze. When frozen, slice and serve as desired. Keeps several weeks in the freezer.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place one pie crust into a greased casserole.
Mix Veg-All, soup and chicken.
Pour into crust.
Place other crust on top of the Veg-All mixture.
Seal with a fork.
Bake at 375° until crusts are golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chill until thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into 4 serving dishes.
Chill until firm (2 hours).
Calories:
4 g, cholesterol:
10 mg, sodium:

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, pepper, celery, onion and peas.
Top with mayonnaise and sugar mixture, making sure all the top is covered. Sprinkle cheese over top of mayonnaise mixture and then crumble bacon.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; stir in sauce, water, basil and oregano. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and egg.
In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 noodles, 1/3 sauce, 1/3 cottage cheese mixture, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat; end with Mozzarella on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add soup, water, and mushrooms (salt and pepper to taste).
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until thick. Add sour cream just before serving over rice.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts and chill 1 hour.
May top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add other ingredients, adding bananas last.
Pour into 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious banana pudding
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Stir in brown sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and water;
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly (about 15-20 minutes).
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir some of hot mixture into yolks; add remaining hot mixture stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes longer or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cool.
Lightly grease 1-3/4 quart casserole; line bottom and sides with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas to cover wafers. Repeat layers.
Pour pudding mixture over this.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Cover pudding with egg whites and place in a 425° oven for 5 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: black beans ham hocks(servings:  4)
directions: Let beans soak overnight.
Chop pepper (bell), onion and garlic; fry lightly with ham hocks, bay leaf and butter until it looks yummy.
Drain bacon and wash.
Combine pan mixture with beans in same juice.
Add hot sauce to taste.
Cook on low 4 to 5 hours or until mushy.
Serve over rice with green onions.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch spring-form pan with margarine.
In a large pot (or microwave), cook apple slices with water and 1/4 cup sugar until apples are just tender. Drain.
In a small bowl, mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and spices. With a pastry blender, cut in 1/2 cup margarine.
Reserve 1 cup of flour mixture for the topping. Cut egg into remainder and press into bottom and sides of pan. Spoon drained apples into pan. Bake for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 12 slices.
Per Slice:
225 total calories; 15 sat-fat calories.

title: chocolate 4-layer dessert
directions: Press in 9 x 13 baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dumplings (16)
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Mix quickly only until blended.
Drop by tablespoons onto chicken or beef stew.
Cook 10 minutes, uncovered, and 10 minutes covered. Sprinkle with parsley when done.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Flatten biscuits on ungreased baking sheet with bottom of floured custard cup.
This will leave a rim.
Fill biscuit centers with onion mixture. Bake in oven following directions on biscuit can.

title: warm spinach salad
directions: In medium bowl, toss spinach, mushrooms and carrots.
Set aside.
In a 9 to 10-inch microwave pie plate, arrange bacon. Cover with paper towel. Microwave on High 3 1/2 minutes or until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Into pie plate, add dressing, blended with mustard.
Microwave on High 1 minute, or until heated through.
Pour over spinach mixture. Add bacon and toss.
Yields 2 servings.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown oil, onion, garlic and turkey, breaking up turkey into small pieces as you cook.
Stir in chili powder, pepper and cumin until well combined.
Strain beans and rinse.

title: 7 layer cookie bar
directions: Layer on melted butter according to listing.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Melt red hots and sugar in the water.
Add other ingredients.

title: mexican pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: oyster soup
directions: Drain oysters thoroughly.
Set aside.
Put oil in pot; add chopped onions; cook until golden.
Add bell pepper, celery and half the green onions.
Cook 10 minutes on low heat.
Add oysters, 1/4 stick butter, remaining green onions, red and black pepper, salt and garlic juice.
Cook until mixture becomes thick.
Add milk slowly and heat rapidly until immediately before milk comes to boiling point.
Remove from heat and stir.
Add remaining butter or enough to coat entire top of mixture.
Add chopped fresh parsley, if desired.
Serve hot in soup bowls with oyster crackers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: happy holiday simmer scent
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer in an open pan on stove top or heat and pour into simmer pot.
Enjoy!

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil.
Drain.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar; add to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly.
Add pork chops and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: fish fillets veronique
directions: Slice the grapes in half and place them in a bowl with the wine and the lemon juice, tossing gently.
Line a broiling pan with foil and arrange the fish in the pan.
Sprinkle the lemon peel and lime juice over the fish.
Top with the ginger, bell pepper and seasoning, except for the garnish.
Broil the fish for about 5 minutes, until the fillets begin to turn golden.
Pour the grape-wine mixture over the fish arranging the grapes cut-side down.
Broil a couple more minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serve with the garnishes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Cut the potato in half. Scoop out the potato. Push potato skin to the side.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Do not drain salmon.
Take out bones, dark skin, etc., and break into chunks.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Turn when brown.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: Cut up onion, carrot, celery and garlic in small pieces and saute in olive oil.
Blend two cans white beans with 1/2 can water in blender.
Combine all ingredients except the pasta in a saucepan and cook on medium heat about 45 minutes.
Prepare pasta according to package directions and mix into soup.
Enjoy!

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Form into balls; roll in flakes (optional).
Brown.
Place in baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg, peanut butter and soda in. Add flour and vanilla.
Roll dough in balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant(serves 2)
directions: Cut top off eggplant and wash and prick with fork.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes to soften.
Let cool.
Cut lengthwise down the middle.
Scoop out seeds and pulp.
Prepare stuffing.
Add onion, eggs and herbs and mix well.
Divide and fill two halves of eggplant.
Brush with egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Brush with oil or butter.
Bake at
350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Slice mushrooms.
Chop onions.
Marinate for 4 hours in salad oil mixture.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Roll biscuit pieces into mixture.
Drop pieces evenly around Pam-sprayed Bundt pan.
Melt the oleo and pour evenly over coated biscuit pieces.
Can pour remaining sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon-apple biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
In a large bowl, using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Do not overblend, overblending fat produces a mealy, rather than flaky tender biscuits.
Mix in apple, cinnamon, sugar and pecans.
Gently push mixture to edges of bowl, making a well in center.
Using a fork, blend in just enough milk so dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Too much milk makes dough hard to handle; too little makes dry biscuits.
Do not overmix.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine green tomatoes, red tomatoes, onions, cabbage and peppers.
Grind and add salt.
Drain.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and spice mix.
Simmer 40 minutes.

title: beef roulades
directions: Cut steak into 12 long pieces; pound with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer.
Place 1/3 cup stuffing on each piece of steak; roll up and fasten with toothpick.
In large skillet, brown in shortening and pour off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover, simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Uncover. Cook until desired consistency.
Serves 12.

title: springtime crustless quiche
directions: Day before serving, rinse spinach well.
Cover with water. Place saucepan over low heat; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir periodically.
Drain well, squeezing out excess moisture.
Chop coarsely; set aside.
Melt butter in small skillet over medium-low heat.
Add shallots; cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, whisk together the milk, eggs, Jack cheese, dill, lemon zest, salt and pepper.
Stir in spinach, tomatoes that have been seeded and chopped and shallots until well combined.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with plastic; refrigerate overnight, or until ready to bake.
In preheated 350° oven, bake quiche, uncovered, for 40 minutes, or until set and browned.
Remove; let stand.

title: lemon-pecan bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in pecans and lemon rind. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until
wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove loaf pan and cool completely.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon about 2-inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 18 minutes.
If you use sweet milk, cut soda to 1/4 teaspoon and use 2 teaspoons of baking powder.
We always had these cookies at Christmas.

title: zippy shrimp spread
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Chill.
Peel and devein.
Set 3 shrimp aside for garnish.
Coarsely chop others.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except for pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix salt, sifted flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour milk into saucepan and add sifted flour mixture.
Stir over heat until very warm.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple.
Mix well and serve.

title: taco chicken casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown 2 pounds cut up stew meat which has been salted, peppered and floured.
Remove from skillet and drain off excess fat.
Return meat to skillet and slice 1 large onion or 2 medium onions.
Cover with water and simmer until meat is tender.
If water gets low, add a little at a time.
When meat and onion are done, remove to dish with slotted spoon.
To remaining broth, add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and 1 cup sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Return meat to mixture and bring to a boil.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: In buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish, place a layer of cubed chicken, bread crumbs, cheese and broccoli.
Combine soup, milk and pepper; pour over mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°; let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream
together
margarine, brown sugar and white sugar. Add eggs
at a time; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sauce for rolls and apple cake
directions: Cook sauce until thick.
Pour over rolls when still hot.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per instructions 7 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and add enough Ranch dressing to suit taste.
Salt to taste.

title: chicken strips
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Mix flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper in a small bowl; coat strips.
Melt butter or margarine in frying pan and saute coated strips for 5 minutes.
Place sauteed strips in baking dish and set aside.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Soak rice with soups and wine overnight. Stir well.
Place rice in baking pan and put chicken on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, then 1/2 hour, uncovered, or until chicken is done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugars, butter and peanut butter well.
Add eggs, flour, soda and vanilla.
Form small balls in palm of hands.
Place in pan.
Dip fork in water; press to flatten.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain. Arrange stalks in a greased 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.

title: cookies from sweden
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift together and stir in: flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in cherries, citron, coconut, orange rind and almond extract.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 7 to 8 dozen, 2-inch cookies.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter until light; blend in molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Brush all sides with Proverbs 31:6 (wine or orange juice).

title: meat loaf
directions: Place in a meat loaf pan.
It is better to use a pan that has a drain rack so meat loaf will not set in the fat.
Cover entire top with ketchup.
Place enough bacon strips to cover top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt the paraffin wax, then add the chocolate chips and mix well. Dip the peanut butter balls into the chocolate and coat well.
Place on wax paper and let dry.
Makes approximately 40 peanut butter balls.

title: cheesy appetizer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unfold pastry and place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cook and stir mushrooms, onion and peppers in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in a saucepan.
Bring to a slow boil, stirring well to keep smooth.
Pour into 1 graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: low-fat custard
directions: Mix together and chill. Tastes like boiled custard.

title: unusual pudding salad
directions: Mix well pudding and Cool Whip, then add fruit.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes or so.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter. mix all other ingredients together. Stir in butter, bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hrs.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together in pan.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then roll in
flour.
Heat oil in large skillet to cover chicken halfway.
When
oil
is
hot,
add chicken and cook until done. Drain on paper towel.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix hominy, soup, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle with corn flake crumbs and butter. Bake at 300° until brown.

title: pickled string beans(from 1975 edition)
directions: French cut and cook the green beans.
While they are cooking, combine water, sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil. Drain cooked beans and put into large jar.
Slice onion thinly over beans.
While still hot, pour liquid over them.
Chill.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets with Crisco. Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put a tablespoon of ham in each chicken breast and roll up. Place in baking dish. Mix together sour cream and mushroom soup. Put a dollop of that mixture on top of each chicken breast. Bake in 350 degree oven for one hour, covered for 45 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes. If the chicken breasts are large, longer baking time may be necessary.

title: peanut buster dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: frog legs
directions: Preheat deep fat to 238°.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Place frog legs in bag.
Shake, coating well.
Remove legs and shake off excess.
Drop in hot fat and fry until golden brown. Drain and serve.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Pour dry jello over cottage cheese; mix well. Drain pineapple and oranges well; add cottage cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: eye round beef roast with tomato gravy
directions: Wash roast and dry well.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil and cook until doneness desired at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
When roast is done, blend tomatoes and flour together. Add to pan drippings.
Cook over medium heat until it is desired thickness.

title: low-fat breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes on bottom of greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon chips.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Bake chicken at 400° for 30 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients (dry first, then add liquid).
Cook, stirring constantly over medium/high heat until thick.
Allow to boil gently for 3 minutes.
Brush over chicken.
Continue baking 40 minutes, basting with sauce every 10 minutes.
Broil the last couple of minutes.
Watch carefully so as not to let burn.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Place ingredients in pot or casserole dish. Top with 2 or 3 slices of bacon. Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: beans
directions: Fast boil beans for about 1 hour, adding water as needed.
Add all other ingredients, chopping tomatoes into smaller pieces.
Use spices according to taste.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature before mixing together.
Form into a ball; place in a bowl lined with waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
About 1 hour before serving, roll ball in chopped pecans and parsley mixed together.
Place on platter and surround with crisp crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer pieces of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour prepared Jell-O over cake.
Add pineapple with juice.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Add pie filling.
Reserve 5 or 6 cherries for garnish. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with reserved cherries and pecan pieces.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine or butter and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. (Mixture will scorch easily.)
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, Karo and melted butter.
Add well beaten eggs, pecans and vanilla.
Turn into an uncooked pie shell.
Cook until firm.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, mushroom soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cram, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can Durkee French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch round pie pan.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well with a fork.
Roll out dough using rolling pin on floured cutting board.
Cut out biscuits. Place in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Spread butter on top while hot.
Pop open while hot and stuff with butter, jelly or gravy of your choice.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Rub a bowl with cut garlic.
Soften cream cheese over hot water in a double boiler.
Transfer to bowl and add all other ingredients.
